5V5 Escort Battle

Victory Conditions:
1. Attackers: Escort the target to the destination within the specified time.
2. Defenders: Prevent the escort target from reaching the destination within the specified time.
Special Mechanics:
1. Move close to or stick on the payload to control its movement.
2. You can adjust the String Energy Network while in a Safe Zone or waiting to respawn.
3. You can resupply your tactical items multiple times.
4. Team members will respawn at the same time periodically.

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Participation Rules: </>Unlock Ranked matches at Lv. 10.

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Season Duration: </>Each season lasts for approximately two months. At the end of each season, you will earn rewards based on the highest rank achieved in the season. At the beginning of each season, you need to play placement matches again to determine your starting rank.

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Ranks: </>There are a total of nine ranks, each with different divisions and Strinovium Point limits (see image above).

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Promotion and Demotion: </>When you reach the maximum number of stars in each division, one more victory will promote you, granting you one star (some exceptional Navigators may skip one additional division upon promotion). After losing all your stars in a division, one more loss will trigger a demotion of divisions or ranks.

<NoticePC_TextBlod>Rank Protection: </>No star loss on defeats in Substance or Molecule ranks; no demotion in Proton rank after losing all stars in a division.

<Rank-Title>1.</> Strinovium points increase or decrease based on performance and match outcome.

2128FE554069B0F3A7F55EB9BB8722F7:
<Rank-Title>1.</> Upon reaching Superstring rank, Ranked matches switch to a points system. Points increase or decrease based on performance and outcome after each match.
<Rank-Title>2.</> On promotion from Quark to Superstring rank, Strinovium Points convert to Superstring Points at a <Rank-Red>20:1</> ratio.
<Rank-Title>3.</> If Superstring Points fall to 0, your first loss triggers rank protection. Another loss will demote you to Quark I.
<Rank-Title>4.</> If you don't play a Ranked match for <Rank-Red>7 consecutive days</>, you'll lose 30 Superstring Points, down to a minimum of 0.
<Rank-Title>5.</> Once you reach 200 Superstring Points, ranking in the top 500 promotes you to Singularity rank. Falling out of the top 500 demotes you back to Superstring rank.
<Rank-Title>6.</> Superstring and Singularity ranked players can only queue solo or as a duo.

ActivityCNYFireStory.4_StoryContext: You join Lawine on the observation deck to watch the fireworks celebrations. The grand display brought out some homesickness in Lawine, making her feel small and lonely. No matter - you're willing to be a safe harbor for drifters.
ActivityCNYFireStory.2_StoryContext: The brave Michele and her partner, the Navigator, embark on an adventure together - a hidden stage that our heroes can't get enough of!
ActivityCNYFireStory.3_StoryContext: Busy with her work, Audrey has been unable to help out with the preparations. To make sure she felt included and to reward her for all her hard work, you decided to join her in the fireworks celebrations.
ActivityCNYFireStory.5_StoryContext: After your busy week helping with the celebration preparations, Kokona invites you to watch the fireworks together. The mighty sea bunny captain uses her makeshift telescope to “see into the future” - for both you and Strinova, the future is sure to get better and better!
ActivityCNYFireStory.1_StoryContext: The celebrations are approaching, and work in the Astral Sanctuary is finally coming to an end. You go to watch the fireworks together, enjoy the beautiful display side by side, and understand each other's feelings without needing to say a word.

ActivityCommonStory.6_StoryContext:
xx Year x Month x Day, Sunday, Clear


Today, while delivering food to Astral Sanctuary, I stumbled upon a new job opportunity:

"Recruiting diving guides for the Summer Isles. Free meals, diving gear, and opportunities for close encounters with marine life."

Summer Isles, underwater ruins, and mysterious treasures...
This rare job (adventure) opportunity is too good to miss~
Just as Celestia asked me to help the Navigator break their bad habit of staying indoors and working overtime, I decided to bring the Navigator along.

To claim the legendary treasure, we must conquer various trials.
For instance, the underwater combat race—how did I pass that level again?
Oh, right, I remember causing a huge underwater inferno, after which the other contestants vanished...
(Note: This was not against the rules!)

But everyone seemed to think it was some kind of magical, new underwater show. Instead of causing panic, the storm brought cheers and applause! This is a real opportunity. The organizers want me to perform the "Deep Sea Inferno" for more audiences, and my hourly wage will jump from 50 to 100 Dream Tokens!

With this, I can save up more quickly to buy Kanami's album!
Current savings progress: 800/3000 Dream Tokens.
Keep going, Eika, you got this~!

Oh, and I've entrusted the treasure map fragments obtained from the trials to the reliable Navigator.
ActivityCommonStory.2_StoryContext:
The young bartender told me her name—Fuchsia, a flower from old Earth. She wasn't secretive about her personal information, yet she spoke with little interest, like a passerby in a hurry, unwilling to leave a trace in others' memories.

"Are you the bartender here?"

She nodded.

"Besides bartending, do you handle other things? Like opening and closing the bar... In other words, were you the first to arrive here today?"

Her eyes turned cautious: "That's private. I can't tell you."

I handed her my detective card with a sincere demeanor. Under my gaze, she relented, turning away awkwardly: "<SalonOutline>Anyway, Meredith—the lady with the hood—wasn't the first to arrive. I opened the door for her.</>”

Then she looked at me again, probing: "<SalonOutline>You get what I mean?</>”

I winked at her, putting a finger to my lips in a "shh" gesture.
ActivityCommonStory.1_Desc:
My eyes wandered around the bar before being quickly drawn to a woman sitting on a single sofa, playing poker.Everything about her screamed “mysterious”, from the smile on her lips and her hidden gaze to her figure flickering under the light. Could this be my client?
 
(Approach her and introduce yourself.)
ActivityCommonStory.2_StoryIntro: The stoic bartender focused on mixing drinks

ActivityConcertLevel.1_LevelRoleContent: “Took you long enough to get here, my savior! Good thing at least you're reliable. I'll be waiting for you in the practice room. Come over soon!”
ActivityConcertLevel.2_LevelRoleContent: “What to do... such an important task left to me... I can't handle it...!”
ActivityConcertLevel.4_LevelRoleContent: “Performing is an idol's specialty! Hehe... Don't worry, Navigator, I won't let you down!”
ActivityConcertLevel.3_LevelRoleContent: “Piano? Don't worry. Just be natural and enjoy the music!”
ActivityConcertLevel.5_LevelRoleContent: “Music brings peace to the mind. I have no objection to your invitation, Navigator. I'll be there.”

ActivityConcertStory.5_Content:
“Navigator! Wait, no... It's 'conductor' now... you're here! Let's get started!”
Kanami's face is full of enthusiasm. Gazing at the practice room mirror, she's long imagined seeing this side of herself, displaying a musical prowess that none could match.
But when she finally saw who she wanted to see, it was in the lounge at night, body covered in a conductor's coat.
“Huh? Did I mess something up? Kanami just wanted to give the Navigator a surprise... After all, Lawine and the other said as much, and even gave me such beautiful clothes...”
Kanami lowers her head, a flurry of emotions on her red face.
Surprise, self-blame, bashfulness...
“A-Are you surprised? I...”
Her face becomes redder, and she fumbles over herself even more.
“I-I'll definitely become your favorite idol!”
The girl speaks while covering her face with a sheet of music. The conductor in front of her gives a simple nod and starts turning to leave.
Feelings were conveyed, albeit with a misunderstanding.
But even so... this still counts as being bold and achieving one's goal... doesn't it?
ActivityConcertStory.6_Content:
“It's you. No need to worry. I'm not the most experienced in classical music, but I'm familiar with music theory.”
When the sunset comes, the lone shadow in the practice room finally comes to a stop.
“Not good enough again... No, I guess it can count as a success. What do you think, Navigator?”
The lone figure keeps their distance, holding their saxophone.
“...I wouldn't feel very comfortable being so close, but if you feel it will help you conduct, I won't voice any complaints.”
Lawine speaks calmly, maintaining a mysterious profile in the sunset.
A calming and nostalgic étude is played once more.
One can't help but be confident that the performance will be one that lingers in the memory.
ActivityConcertStory.3_Content:
“Bai Mo suddenly dumped this task on me. I'm really a little... uh... unconfident.”
In the practice room, Maddelena looks at me with a violin in her hand. Through her glasses, I can see a lost look on her pale and youthful face.
“I really... uhm... what if my sister sees? Eh...? Just let you guide me? Treat it as a paintbrush...?”
Instead of replying, I simply raise my baton and start conducting with the score. Maddelena makes a lot of harsh and pained sounds, and it takes till dark for us to get the atmosphere right.
“Can you feel it, Navigator? In this way, even someone ordinary like me can keep up with someone like Bai Mo...!”
She's got it the wrong way around. The ordinary timbre is the most important part of any performance. Without the violin's thread, the entire performance may as well be empty talk.
Maddelena's shy smile gives off the airs of a reserved calmness that is hers alone. With it, one can't help but be intoxicated by the sound of the music...
ActivityConcertStory.4_Content:
Outside the practice room, I hear the sound of piano movements slowly flowing out from a crack in the door.
Even after I open the door, the girl remains focused. Her light, slender fingers dance along the black and white keys, continuing until they strike the last note on a black.
“Music is fascinating. It's so different from medicine and anything else I've dabbled in. It's so easy to get drawn in without even noticing.”
As she speaks, she lifts the little hat on her head and shoots me a playful wink.
“Want to try piano four hands? You won't be able to conduct properly without giving it a go.”
Before I can react, Kokona pulls me to her side.
“Don't worry, just follow my lead.”
Our melody steadily blooms into a cheerful dance of keys.
Kokona might be right. If you spend all your time on the podium, you lose sight of the full picture.
“I'm looking forward to the performance. If we could continue playing together in the future... I think I'd like that.”
There's a hint of caring expectation in her smile...
ActivityConcertStory.7_Content:
Standing on the podium and looking into the packed crowd, you feel surprisingly at ease.
You know that each and every member of your band has great faith in you.
The next step is to just raise your baton and kick off a grand performance. With the music of the new year, the band will bid the past farewell and welcome blessings anew.
This serves as both an invitation and a hope for joyful news.
We wish you happiness, all of you who love Strinova.
ActivityConcertStory.2_Content:
When I arrived at the practice room, I found Bai Mo already perched in a chair, hard at work on his études, glancing at me through the corner of his eye.
“What do you think, friend? A good pitch, is it not?”
I must admit that Bai Mo is quite the accomplished musician. Knowing his unreliable nature, it's hard to imagine he could be as elegant and gentle as he is now.
“Come and conduct. Let's have a proper practice performance.”
I raise my baton and extend an invitation for him to begin.
“Alright! Check this out!”
The tuba becomes spirited, moving in lockstep with the conductor's baton and leading the rhythm - most fitting for Bai Mo, indeed.
“Capital, my friend! But now is not the time to trade compliments. There is still much work to be done.”
The corners of his mouth are raised in expectation. It seems that he has all the faith in the world that I'll make this a success.
ActivityConcertStory.7_Title: Finale: Thank You for a Successful Performance
ActivityConcertStory.1_Content:
At the start of the new year, a special invitation from Urbino was handed to you.
This message comes from Bai Mo, head of the Urbino Business Alliance. Having been inspired to celebrate the New Year with music, Bai Mo has called for talented musicians from far and wide to participate in the event.
Yet Bai Mo has greatly underestimated the opinions of these talented individuals, and their rift I fear is so great as to have destroyed any promise of this great performance. It is for this reason I especially wanted to pass this letter to you...
“There's no time, my friend. Only you can help me now! Only you can put these weirdos... Ahem, I mean, only you can get everyone on the same page to make this performance a success. I'm counting on you!”
                                               - Bai Mo

ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_EndDesOne: There's no rush. The game is similar to chess. You have to carefully plan your every move. I'm happy to practice with you for a few rounds before the real match.

ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.2_EndDesOne: Head lowered, sighing... Signs of frustration... According to my records, coffee improves your win rate. Would you like some?
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.2_GameOpen: Your mood swings and reactions during the game are among the things I wish to record... Start the challenge. I'll make sure to record everything.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.2_EndDesTwo: Commendable. You've solved most of the puzzles... I am curious about your reaction when you've solved them all.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.2_EndDesThree: Perfect, flawless deduction... There are a lot more things I have to record. You, for one, are a most fascinating puzzle.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_GameOpen: Heh. Don't be nervous. Let's play a game to help you relax. Can you see through the puzzle?
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.2_DesFirst: Oh, my identity?... I'm just an ordinary butler who's interested in records.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.3_EndDesThree: We've finished deep cleaning. Rewards, you say? I don't know. Will bullets do?
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.3_DesSecond: Duties of a maid...? Got it. Cleaning and picking up trash. I'm a fast learner.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_EndDesThree: As I've expected, you're an excellent player... In that case, I'll tell you a little secret as a reward.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.3_DesThird: If you're late again... You can imagine what will happen to the dust...
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.2_DesThird: Yes, I'm recording. Don't mind me. It's my job to record everything that takes place in the café.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_DesThird: The only thing I can tell you, Navigator, is that you're safe now. No one will interrupt us... Heh. Would you like to know more?
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_DesFirst: Surprised, are you? Butterflies come to the café to stretch their wings from time to time.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_DesSecond: Do you wonder what I've prepared for you? Step into the game. You're a key piece in it.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.3_GameOpen: Bummer. My weapons have been confiscated. Let's try some basic challenges.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.3_EndDesOne: The dirt hasn't been cleaned yet... You need special training for maids. I'll teach you how to clean properly.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.1_EndDesTwo: Shame. You were so close... Take a break. Have a cup of coffee. I'll give you a hint.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.2_DesSecond: Record, think, deduct. These things come to me as natural and as necessary as breathing.
ActivityMaid2RoleOpen.3_EndDesTwo: Not bad. Next time, let's clean the remaining dirt together.

ActivityStrangeThiefStory.23_ContentAside:
- Multiple clue cards mention surveillance footage. Who installed the cameras?
     - “Me, the mastermind, of course. I knew exactly where everyone was.”

- Did you really forget about the time? How did you manage to show up at the exact moment Lawine entered Kidd Hall?
     - “Why do you think I had cameras installed, Navigator? As a competent member of the Phantom Thieves, I adjusted my time of arrival based on the situation to ensure the item would be unveiled on time.”

- Why did you plan a bomb? I don't get it.
     - “Because I wanted something fun! Besides, I had to blow up the surveillance devices and the secret passage. I wasn't going to tell everyone that Kanami and the gang stole the final auction item.”

- Had I failed to solve the puzzle in time, would you still have detonated the bomb?
     - “While I had other methods to take out the cameras without the risk of injuries, Navigator, I knew what you were capable of. A simple puzzle was a piece of cake for you.”

- Does that mean you gave Ming the details of the auction item?
     - “Not bad. Did you notice my call? Besides that, I was also the person responsible for the secret passage. I'd wanted them to have the item for a while. It was more fun than purchasing it and giving it to them.”

- What about the codes on the clue cards? According to your plan, Lawine and the others wouldn't have known about you.
     - “You figured that out as well, Navigator? Well, I thought it would be cool, that's all. You know me. I'm an indispensable member of the Phantom Thieves. The family has to stay together.”

- Was the self-portrait of Mr. Black Cat a part of your plan as well?
     - “How dare you... No, certainly not. I could never have expected it! They've ruined my reputation...”

- What exactly was the final auction item?
     - “I can't tell you. Why don't you ask The Scissors? Hahahaha!”

Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Not just sugar... Adding some whey protein and tea polyphenols would make things even better.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId131: It wasn't me. Fay was the one who said it...
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId131: If possible... easily absorbable liquid nutrients would be best.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row14_PlayerOption1: Sounds like... Yvette wants to have some milk tea?
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Navigator, do you know any good sources of sugar?
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row11_PlayerOption1: For acute blood sugar problems, we can administer glucose directly.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row17_PlayerOption2: I just happened to have a ticket to the Sweet Dreams Amusement Park.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row4_PlayerOption2: Are you working too hard? Make sure to take a break once in a while.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId131: It's no problem for now. But it is dangerous.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Fay... I'm really demotivated right now. I can't think of anything.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Fay says we need some more energy-dense carbohydrates.
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row17_PlayerOption1: Speaking of which, have you heard anything about the “Journey of Dreams” event at the amusement park?
Amusement_334_Lv_1.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId131: If this goes on, I won't be able to do any research at all.

Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row25_TextContent_FromRoleId101: No, no, no! It's nothing! I must have made a mistake!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row18_PlayerOption1: That's what you expect from the number one investigator.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Otherwise, I'd definitely have asked you to play!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId101: The amusement park is really lively today.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row14_PlayerOption1: How'd you end up helping out at the candy shop?
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Guess where I am right now?
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Heheh... I knew you wouldn't get it!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row20_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Well... except for some reports of a strange bear-like creature with a knack for sweets, there's nothing too special to report.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Hehe... You may have overstated its power a bit...
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row22_TextContent_FromRoleId101: So long as I can see the smile on everyone's faces while helping out, then I didn't come in vain.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Many of the rides have been decorated to resemble desserts.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row3_PlayerOption1: Michele would usually be at home gaming.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row9_PlayerOption1: I just happened to get an entry ticket from someone else...
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId101: I'm helping out at the amusement park's candy shop.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId101: That's why I offered to come in and assist as a plainclothes investigator.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row18_PlayerOption2: Have you discovered any safety concerns?
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId101: There's a cupcake Ferris wheel and a donut bumper car... I feel like I'm dreaming!
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row23_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Sure enough... Even The Scissors wouldn't destroy such a sweet dream.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId101: There are so many customers at the candy shop... I can't even take a breather...
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId101: I didn't show off my investigator skills this time, but...
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId101: The event has attracted so many visitors that the amusement park's security can't keep up.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Then you've gotta come visit Michele's candy shop.
Amusement_334_Lv_2.Row26_TextContent_FromRoleId101: Then I'll make my way over there first. Bye-bye!

Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Kanami's heart raced with excitement at the prospect of meeting the Navigator by chance!
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row24_TextContent_FromRoleId137: I wonder... did that child have sweet dreams?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId137: But, along the way, there were so many wonderful sights and incredible desserts that I totally forgot about searching for the Navigator...
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row20_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Today, I saw that ticket with my signature on it in the crowd.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId137: The tour should nearly be over, right?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId137: I just wanted to know how you would react, Navigator.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Hehe! I tricked you! I know you already gave away the tickets.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Hehe! We should be thanking the power of destiny!
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Before this short-lived dream ends, make sure you don't have any regrets! ☆
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId137: How about the “Journey of Dreams” event at the amusement park? Did you find it interesting?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId137: I'm right outside the candy shop, looking over the Ferris wheel.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId137: So... could you spend those final moments with Kanami?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row22_PlayerOption1: I'm sorry that it didn't meet your expectations.
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row23_TextContent_FromRoleId137: It's fine! As an idol, I just want to be the bearer of dreams! ☆
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Have you been to all the popular check-in spots?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Have you tried all their special desserts?
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Winning a special prize at a Kanami fan meetup... this is proof of the Navigator's love for me!
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row25_TextContent_FromRoleId137: And... next time, you better not run away from Kanami again!
Amusement_334_Lv_3.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId137: Kanami also snuck her way into the amusement park!

ApartmentBirthdaySeasonComments.3_Desc: Are you an autumn baby too? Let's take a trip to the countryside together and soak in the beauty of the fall scenery.
ApartmentBirthdaySeasonComments.1_Desc: So... your birthday's in spring? It's a perfect season for an outing together in such warm weather.
ApartmentBirthdaySeasonComments.2_Desc: On summer nights, the stars twinkle endlessly. Maybe we could watch them together sometime.
ApartmentBirthdaySeasonComments.4_Desc: When it's time to celebrate your birthday, we can also have a snowball fight together~

ApartmentMapCfg.1001_Desc: Strinova Guide at your service. Please do not try gliding after drinking sparkling water.
ApartmentMapCfg.124_Desc: Kokona briefly served in the P.U.S training unit, but she prefers frontline work.
ApartmentMapCfg.128_Desc: Lawine had her personnel file redacted when she left P.U.S. No one even knows her true name...
ApartmentMapCfg.137_Desc: Visit the idol singer Kanami in her home. It must feel magical.
ApartmentMapCfg.146_Desc: Celestia's Astral Sanctuary is a major investment project of Urbino.
ApartmentMapCfg.112_Desc: The mysterious mercenary girl gave her address to you and only you. This shows how much you mean to her.
ApartmentMapCfg.105_Desc: Grove Bank is an important asset of the Grove Family and Audrey's pride.
ApartmentMapCfg.101_Desc: As the governing body of Strinova, P.U.S enforces strict discipline, with all members residing in assigned dormitories.
ApartmentMapCfg.131_Desc: Whenever asked about her address, Yvette quickly provides the location of the P.U.S dormitory before nervously clutching the hem of her clothes...
ApartmentMapCfg.107_Desc: Maddelena believes that designers are always either creating or seeking inspiration!

ApartmentMapLoadingTips.15_Tips: “This is the song of my soul, the gift I would like to offer the world♪” - Kanami
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.54_Tips: Yvette has a mysterious past... Perhaps she is waiting for someone she can open up to.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.52_Tips: Yvette prefers cold beverages and desserts, but she has never fallen ill because of them.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.57_Tips: Yvette offers to make Fay all kinds of clothes, but Fay refuses every time. Yet, Yvette does not intend to give up.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.16_Tips: Yvette is familiar with all sorts of creatures and helps them survive in this world.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.22_Tips: As the head of Astral Sanctuary, she is respected by all healthcare workers, yet she remains humble and kind.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.14_Tips: Nobunaga wakes up each day in pain, haunted by his kin's betrayal.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.20_Tips: A healer cannot heal herself; Celestia needs a doctor too when she treats others.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.19_Tips: She has spent countless nights observing and waiting. Will the stars ever respond to her?
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.42_Tips: If you're unsure what takeout to order, ask Kokona—she'll have a special recommendation.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.12_Tips: In the dead of night, Reiichi always seems to be kind and gentle.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.55_Tips: At work, Yvette is always calm and rational, seemingly unaffected by anything...
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.34_Tips: As a capitalist, Audrey isn't fully mature yet, still holding onto the weakness of kindness.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.30_Tips: Audrey often talks about her family.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.32_Tips: Audrey's firepower and sharp mind are her greatest weapons.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.5_Tips: Audrey once suffered from Collapse Syndrome, but she still managed to piece herself back together with the help of her diary and the kindness of others.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.29_Tips: Audrey's crown is a family heirloom and symbol. Its shiny, tough exterior encases a soft, pure core, embodying the essence of family.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.31_Tips: Though she can analyze situations rationally and stay calm through any change, her blushing reveals everything when she's complimented.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.21_Tips: The stars she lights up become the path for those who follow.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.49_Tips: If you're seeking artistic surprises in life, contact designer Maddelena Leary.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.10_Tips: Chase your dream if you still have one, for all dreams can be realized right here!
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.65_Tips: Fuchsia is capable of completely hiding her presence when necessary.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.46_Tips: To Maddelena, her art consultant is also her best model.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.44_Tips: Kokona's strong drive and proactiveness come from her innate curiosity, always open to trying unusual dishes.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.45_Tips: Kokona excels at taking care of others emotionally, but she rarely allows herself to be cared for.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.41_Tips: Kokona's room is always cluttered with random items, so watch your step when visiting.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.7_Tips: Kokona claims the secret to staying energized is smiling a lot.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.37_Tips: It's obvious that Lawine and the impulsive Ming are complementary to one another. On the battlefield, they inspire their teammates' fighting spirit.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.39_Tips: Clenching the Pulse Blade, showing its sharp edge in the dark of the night, Lawine tells herself to bid farewell to the past.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.6_Tips: Lawine is an outstanding budo practitioner, thanks to her childhood experiences.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.38_Tips: Formerly one of the top investigators of P.U.S, Lawine had a bright future.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.36_Tips: Lawine enjoys drinking tea, especially green tea.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.35_Tips: Lawine is meticulous and diligent, two contributing factors to her becoming an enforcer of The Scissors.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.40_Tips: Lawine hones her body and mind through budō, dispelling her doubts.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.50_Tips: Legend has it that the tiny Maddelena can be seen gathering materials for her art all around the world.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.48_Tips: When people hear the name Ms. Leary, they usually think of Maddelena's older sister, a renowned artist.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.24_Tips: On countless nights, Michele lies in bed wide awake, contemplating the meaning of justice.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.9_Tips: The fire in Ming's eyes has never been extinguished. As a child, she protected the weak with her fists. Nowadays, she points her gun at oppressors.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.11_Tips: Celestia still gets upset when dealing with disobedient patients.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.1_Tips: Celestia still gets upset when dealing with disobedient patients.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.3_Tips: Celestia likes drinking coffee in hopes that its rich aroma will dispel her internal conflict.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.17_Tips: Celestia tweaks her coffee mix daily, to the point where she's lost count of all the variations.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.59_Tips: Kanami's dream started from her desire to shine.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.63_Tips: A song is a record of life. Kanami sings for the silent unseen.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.27_Tips: Michele's father left her Mighty Meow as a companion, who is always there to support and care for Michele.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.25_Tips: Michele's father is her greatest role model and the kind of person she strives to be.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.66_Tips: The solitary Fuchsia has no concept of or attachment to family.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.47_Tips: Maddelena believes that designers are always either creating or seeking inspiration!
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.8_Tips: Maddelena's world is simple—create beautiful art and let everyone enjoy this new realm.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.51_Tips: The majority of Maddelena's designs arise from accidents and troubles.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.13_Tips: Bai Mo has a spray can gifted to him by his best friend. He uses it to leave behind his mark of memories and liberty in the True Wilderness.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.28_Tips: Michele doesn't enjoy solo missions, always hoping someone would accompany her on her adventures.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.4_Tips: Michele is a passionate gamer and the holder of multiple video game world records.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.23_Tips: Michele loves cats, although she has yet to keep one as a pet.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.26_Tips: Michele often emerges victorious by breaking rules, but she has to write a self-reflection report as a disciplinary procedure for it.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.56_Tips: Her colleagues often ask to borrow Fay. A people pleaser, Yvette agrees most of the time. But she always feels uneasy whenever Fay is away.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.68_Tips: Fuchsia sometimes acts childishly, though she is unaware of it, and others don't dare tell her...
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.64_Tips: Fuchsia favors food with a mild flavor that quickly replenishes energy, such as chocolate.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.18_Tips: Though your encounter was by chance, for Celestia, it was a meaningful inevitability.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.43_Tips: Although Kokona enjoys bustling places, she excels in solo operations.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.67_Tips: While she appears slim, Fuchsia is much stronger than you might think.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.2_Tips: Superstrings are individuals who are battle-hardened, constantly evolving, and possess special abilities.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.53_Tips: In crowds, Yvette goes into stealth to avoid potential social interactions. This tactic seems to be quite effective.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.60_Tips: Here's a secret about Kanami: she takes baths at home when she feels stressed.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.33_Tips: Behind her heavy firepower are trustworthy teammates and a belief that must be protected at all costs.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.62_Tips: Kanami has always wanted to sing a song she wrote herself.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.61_Tips: Kanami tends to hide her thoughts and emotions. She hopes you understand her vulnerability.
ApartmentMapLoadingTips.58_Tips: Kanami was born to be an idol. Her looks, aura, and voice are all top-notch.

Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Since this is the first time we're having tea since becoming allies, it's important to have something delicious.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row10_PlayerOption2: Even as a dessert lover, I...
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I feel like we're missing something... Oh, we haven't ordered the drinks yet.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId105: The mousse cake and fruit tart also have great reviews...
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I know a great place we can get some afternoon tea.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId105: There's nothing wrong with having afternoon tea for dinner. I've done it a few times myself.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.RowNewRow_0_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Delete the records according to the actual situation.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Too many desserts? We can always order something else.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Just tell me what you want to eat. It's all on me.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId105: There are tons of flavors - mango, blueberry, matcha, chocolate, and more... Why don't we give them all a try?
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Ally, here is my contact information.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row5_PlayerOption1: I happen to be free, as well.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Today's one of those rare days I don't have any work to do. Would you like to have some tea together?
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row10_PlayerOption1: I'm a bit worried that I ruined my appetite...
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Their salmon sandwich and blueberry scones are delicious. They've become favorites of mine.
Audrey_105_Lv_1.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I made a reservation and got us a good window seat.

Audrey_105_Lv_3.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Last time, I went to an art exhibition.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row17_TextContent_FromPlayer: I can feel it... even without all those abstract paintings.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But they enjoy a solid reputation in the industry.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But this is abstract art. More specifically, it's abstract geometricism.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId105: You should have gotten it by now.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Interest is something that can be developed with time.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Ah... is it really not necessary?
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I felt as if I'd never really given you anything, so I got you ten pieces.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row9_PlayerOption2: Are you sure that it wasn't drawn with a compass and ruler?
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Most people seem to have this first impression. I can understand why.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Giving gifts is a tricky business.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row9_PlayerOption1: Can you tell me what these circles and squares mean...?
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: It may be the work of a new artist.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row16_PlayerOption1: When it comes to gifts, the feelings you express are what matters.
Audrey_105_Lv_3.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId105: My consultant showed me a super interesting painting. I thought you might like it, too.

Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId105: After we visited Café Reminiscence, I thought...
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId105: It's almost the raw flavor of coffee beans, tasting of unprocessed sourness and bitterness!
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId105: So... you prepared this for me?
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Hmm... It's got a unique name.
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I'm clearly enjoying the coffee right now.
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId105: No, I'm saying it's quite unique. I didn't know coffee with a taste this strong existed!
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I thought it'd be nice to have coffee every now and then.
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row5_1_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I didn't expect to receive a return gift so soon.
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row2_PlayerOption1: I've prepared a serving for you
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row12_PlayerOption1: You don't have to finish it...
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row2_PlayerOption2: This is the Astral Sanctuary's signature drink
Audrey_105_Lv_5.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: The taste of the coffee is rather “special...”
Audrey_105_Lv_5.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Did you send me this box of ver.23.8.19.62 Starlight Coffee?

Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId105: “Where are the rest of my kind?” the unicorn ponders in sadness...
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But... I just happen to have a storybook with me.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row16_TextContent_FromRoleId105: According to legends, a beautiful unicorn lives in this forest...
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But I haven't been drinking much coffee as of late.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row8_PlayerOption2: I heard that counting sheep also helps
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId105: When drinking this type of coffee, one shouldn't be surprised if they stay awake for several days.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId105: No animals dare to approach it due to its uniqueness.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Ally, it's been a while since you've written back.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row12_PlayerOption2: I might just fall asleep before you do...
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: It was your suggestion, after all.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Ally, have you ever been troubled by insomnia?
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row23_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Amazing! Bedtime stories seem like a great way to deal with insomnia.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row12_PlayerOption1: Wait a moment... you want to tell me a bedtime story?
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId105: This is how you coax a child to sleep...
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I guess that counts as a success.
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row8_PlayerOption1: Want to try a bedtime story?
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Besides medication, do you have any other good cures?
Audrey_105_Lv_7.Row3_PlayerOption1: The first thing is to stop drinking so much Starlight Coffee.

Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I shouldn't have read bedtime stories.
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId105: But, if you happen to be interested...
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId105: So I decided to rummage through every bookcase in the house.
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId105: The author was trying to be mysterious, so they never wrote an ending.
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId105: My insomnia has only gotten worse.
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row17_TextContent_FromPlayer: How did things suddenly become so heavy?
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId105: Nothing like that... I'm the same as always.
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I can't tell you just yet.
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row4_PlayerOption1: Reading a bedtime story... can't sleep?
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId105: I really want to know... In the end, did the unicorn find its own kind?
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId105: And I ended up doing some spring cleaning.
Audrey_105_Lv_9.Row20_TextContent_FromRoleId105: See you later, then. Don't be late.

AVGEvent.1012_ExtendPerformanceList_Index0_TextPa: Constructs and commanders, your brave choices will give us the spark we need to rekindle this dark night.

AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214646_From_Role146: I really enjoyed spending tonight with you. I couldn't have asked for a better Spring Blessing gift. I hope you'll find my gift to your liking, too.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212420_PlayerOption_ToRole124: Let's watch some real fireworks together!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210143_From_Role101: I'll continue to work hard in the future!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212821_PlayerOption_ToRole128: No need. Lawine is fine the way she is.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210522_From_Role105: You want to take me somewhere else?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210137_PlayerOption_ToRole101: I guess you have a point.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214604_From_Role146: But... will you also be busy with the celebration preparations today?
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212820_From_OtherRole: But I wonder... would it be too conspicuous to go out with you like this? Maybe I need to put on a disguise...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210149_From_Role101: Still, I'm satisfied for now. No matter how beautiful the journey may be, heroes need to keep moving forward.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210749_PlayerOption_ToRole107: Just capture it in your memory.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210133_From_Role101: So we were headed to the rooftop...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210711_From_Role107: The goal of the inspiration collection team? To make a splash at the fireworks celebrations!
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210144_From_Role101: To ensure that people can attend the fireworks celebrations next year and the year after that, and so that everyone can feel the joy we did...
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104212845_From_OtherRole: Why don't you open the gift once you're home? If you like what I picked out, just leave me a note.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104214633_PlayerOption_ToRole146: There will be many more opportunities in the days to come.
AVGEvent_Activity.Row104210145_From_Role101: I'll continue to work hard in the future!

AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203001_Aside_AboutRole105: (Sitting at a table in Café Reminiscence.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204020_Aside_AboutRole105: (Sitting at a table in Café Reminiscence.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102025_Aside_AboutRole105: (Handbag in her hand, Audrey took me to a park at the intersection of the nearby block.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102043_Aside_AboutRole105: (As the sun set, I found my thoughts drifting with the golden light, back to the girl before me.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203047_Aside_AboutRole105: (There was a sudden glimmer in the representatives' eyes. They seemed to be wondering why the head of the Grove family and her partner were so interested in a little store like this.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203072_Aside_AboutRole105: (Once the representatives bid farewell, a tired Audrey sat down beside me. As a show of thanks, the shopkeeper told us everything was on house.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203049_Aside_AboutRole105: (Two cups of coffee cherry wine were quickly served, but the representatives, accustomed to the smoother taste of black tea, remained unconvinced. According to our plan, Audrey would play the role of the “white unicorn” and speak first.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204054_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey remained silent after that. The medals, one black and one white, shone calmy on our chests.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102059_Aside_AboutRole105: (Afterwards, Audrey and I spend a long time taking a walk through the park.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202045_Aside_AboutRole105: (It may not match the greatest chocolates in the world, but in both texture and taste, you immediately feel the chef’s dedication.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102044_Aside_AboutRole105: (The barriers to the girl's heart were slowly breaking away; her rhythm carried the sun's warmth.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202034_Aside_AboutRole105: (She got things twisted again, but at least she's started opening up.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102050_Aside_AboutRole105: (And yet, the hard shell that once protected her had faded away.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204001_Aside_AboutRole105: (It had been a few days since I was last at Café Reminiscence. The shopkeeper has asked us to meet them in front of the café, but it seems closed right now.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202044_Aside_AboutRole105: (The cold and sugary shell dissolves in the mouth, spreading the faint aroma of cherry wine across the tip of the tongue, while the tang of sweet and sour cherry perfectly complemented the richness of the dark chocolate.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102002_Aside_AboutRole105: (The anxious girl seems to have been waiting for a long time, but no matter her expectations, it's not in her character to express anything directly.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204041_Aside_AboutRole105: (As the medal reflected in Audrey's green eyes, her face betrayed a child-like expression, if only for a moment.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201021_Aside_AboutRole105: (After a morning of hard work, we made our way to the entrance of a café.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202042_PlayerOption_ToRole105: (I pop one of the chocolates into my mouth.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102042_Aside_AboutRole105: (In that place, a new and warm world awaits.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202049_PlayerOption_ToRole105: (I pop another piece of the chocolates in Audrey's mouth.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202001_Aside_AboutRole105: (Still worried about improving her popularity, Audrey has summoned me to her dorm once more.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202039_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey removed the chilled chocolates from the fridge. Some were shaped like a four-leaf clover, while others resembled a flower. Though their taste was still a mystery, the effort that went into them was clear to see.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203063_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey passes a copy of her market research to everyone at the table.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203002_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey opens a delicate, elegant metal box filled with fragrant chocolates.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203020_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey took out her phone and seemed to be messaging someone.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201060_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey takes a sip with great caution.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203078_Aside_AboutRole105: (After filling the cup with coffee, she picked the cup up and gestured to me with the same hand.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203055_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey picked up a finely crafted bone china coffee cup, filled it with coffee cherry wine, and toasted the representatives.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202018_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey was too focused on the piles of ingredients to pay me much mind.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203031_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey drew closer to me than usual and lowered her voice.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203075_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey gazed silently at the coffee cup she had pulled out during her speech. Did she want to drink from that one?)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102038_Aside_AboutRole105: (Her voice was gentle and solemn, and as soon as she finished speaking, pure chords embraced the reverberation of the violin's strings and danced across the air.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102027_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey bends down to open her bag and produce a violin.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204004_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey's thoughts were still fully on getting Café Reminiscence the funding it needs. But originally, the reason we came here was to...)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202014_Aside_AboutRole105: (On her desk stood stacks of chocolate recipe books, listing over ten different cooking methods, along with various shapes and styles. It's clear that she's put a lot of effort into getting the chocolates just right.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203057_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey turned her gaze to me, signaling that it was time for the “black unicorn” to speak.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202015_Aside_AboutRole105: (I wonder what the feelings behind these chocolates are? Looking at all the books laid out, I felt a gentle warmth in my heart. All of a sudden, I started looking forward to how they would turn out.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102020_Aside_AboutRole105: (Her green eyes had lit up, accentuating a bright smile.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204055_Aside_AboutRole105: (As she stares at her newly acquired medal, Audrey’s face resembles that of a child who has just opened a present.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203069_Aside_AboutRole105: (Once the dialogue ends, the two representatives whisper among themselves, then turn to us with a tentative expression.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204035_From_Role105: (Whispering) Hey, aren't you playing your role a bit too seriously?
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102049_Aside_AboutRole105: (The uncertainty in the girl's voice blended into the sound of her violin, almost as if she had never spoken the words at all.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204016_Aside_AboutRole105: (Despite Audrey's attempt to explain herself, I could easily glimpse the truth from the panicked expression in her eyes...)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203070_Aside_AboutRole105: (They seemed extremely anxious, but they gave no clear answer. All they asked was that Audrey negotiate with the shopkeeper and leave some time for a follow-up inspection.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203007_Aside_AboutRole105: (Despite Audrey's calm voice, her dainty hands were covered with ingredients. She must have gone through many attempts before settling on this batch.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202057_Aside_AboutRole105: (Though her tone was a little forced, the smile on her face spoke volumes. Audrey had poured all her warm emotions into these chocolates.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203038_Aside_AboutRole105: (The elderly gentleman looked towards me and pushed up his glasses.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204032_Aside_AboutRole105: (The shopkeeper takes out a document, reads it out with some discomfort, then shifts his attention to me.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204025_Aside_AboutRole105: (The shopkeeper looked at us with a pained expression.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105203034_Aside_AboutRole105: (Two customers, a young woman, and an older man, entered the store, both dressed in business attire. The man was particularly well-pruned and wore a unicorn medal on his chest.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204039_Aside_AboutRole105: (The shopkeeper took out two unicorn badges, one black and one white, each overflowing with the pride and purity of the storied family.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102045_Aside_AboutRole105: (As the two of us enjoyed the open square, it felt as if the unicorn was seeking a companion.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202019_Aside_AboutRole105: (She obviously plans to make more than one type of chocolate, but this is way too much work for one person.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102026_Aside_AboutRole105: (The park was as peaceful as one would expect for this lazy afternoon. Only the sound of gentle sprinklers broke the silence.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201051_Aside_AboutRole105: (Audrey and I reach an uncomfortable deadlock. Audrey casts her eyes downward as the coffee cherry wine’s lasting aroma drifts up toward us. She still seems reluctant to give it a try.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202036_Aside_AboutRole105: (We stayed in the kitchen the entire day. If there was even the slightest problem, Audrey would throw out the batch and move on to something else. By the time we were done, there were only a few recipes left.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102001_Aside_AboutRole105: (Inside Audrey's dorm on a warm and sunny day.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102052_Aside_AboutRole105: (Once the performance ended, the night quickly fell.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201017_Aside_AboutRole105: (But her attempts at “making friends” proved less than successful. Even when she was still in the middle of her loquacious introductions, the passers-by would quickly excuse themselves after hearing Audrey's name.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102014_Aside_AboutRole105: (I'm unable to read the glimmer in her eyes. It could have something to do with that musical score mentioned earlier, or perhaps it's the answer to one of the unicorn's stories...)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201056_PlayerOption_ToRole105: (I hand Audrey the cup of coffee.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202012_Aside_AboutRole105: (Things still don't feel quite right, but in any case, the stubborn Audrey being willing to change her mind is definitely a step in the right direction.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202048_Aside_AboutRole105: (Though there's a hint of awkwardness on the surface, Audrey's eyes flash with a hidden expectation.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105202035_Aside_AboutRole105: (Once the hot melted chocolate is poured into the mold, the rich liquid is transformed into various shapes and sizes with the help of some special tools and a little ingenuity.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201001_Aside_AboutRole105: (While I was out, Audrey asked me to help survey her popularity amongst the people of Strinova.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102011_Aside_AboutRole105: (While she was talking, Audrey placed an oversized handbag down behind her. I wonder what could be inside...)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105204017_Aside_AboutRole105: (It was clear that sentimentality was what truly drove her to save the café.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102051_Aside_AboutRole105: (The lonely unicorn disappeared. What remained was the girl, her eyebrows furrowed as she continued to play.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105201016_Aside_AboutRole105: (And so the inspired negotiator applied their unique insights to try and make friends with one stranger after another.)
AVGEvent_Audrey.Row105102040_Aside_AboutRole105: (As Audrey hummed, the last unicorn from the fairy tale galloped in the direction of the flying notes.)

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202097_From_Role124001: The thirty-second mark was just a basic passing grade.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204119_From_OtherRole: “Bunny Mark got more than one parent. Next time, don't you dare try to scrap him without a single word!”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204102_From_OtherRole: “...A few days ago, someone going by the title of “Navigator” came to me with a badly damaged bot.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204106_From_OtherRole: “Whether it comes to worrying about an exam or deciding to become an investigator all on your own... you worry about it alone, never discuss it with anyone, and make the decision all by yourself!”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204110_From_OtherRole: “But, even if you want to be a hero, why don't you tell us when you were struggling?”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204108_From_OtherRole: “You're just 'Kokona', a little brat who likes to show off!”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204114_From_OtherRole: “When I repaired the bot, it became clear to me... you never realized the importance of all its combat logs!”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204103_From_OtherRole: “Seeing all the marks from field use and maintenance... It made me realize how hard you must have been working. But you're just trying to go it alone again!”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204117_From_OtherRole: “The design data of each module has been stored in this projector. We've done the assembly - you just need to finish up the fine-tuning.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204098_From_OtherRole: “Haha... We all have much to say, but allow me to speak for everyone for now.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204113_From_OtherRole: “Hmpf! There's still so many things I want to say, but this will have to suffice for now.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204122_From_OtherRole: “And don't forget, we've all left you a message! Don't forget to listen to them when you're home!”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204111_From_OtherRole: “Even if it's not us, you have many trustworthy companions by your side, right?”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204096_From_OtherRole: “Kokona, you may have graduated, but you're still just a kid.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204104_From_OtherRole: “Kokona, did you forget why I dragged you kicking and screaming into this club?”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204115_From_OtherRole: “I'm working at the AI Institute now. This is exactly the kind of data we need to train our new models.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204107_From_OtherRole: “I couldn't stand it! What do you think you are? A genius? A hero? That's not it...”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204118_From_OtherRole: “This new Sea Bunny drone - 'Bunny Mark' is now yours! In all the battles you've been through together, you've given him a soul.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204116_From_OtherRole: “I've installed a new intelligent core in your bot, while Elise and your mentor have improved the design of the basic framework.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204105_From_OtherRole: “Even though you were always smiling and seemed to get along with everyone... I could tell you were hiding so many things in your heart.”
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204121_From_Role124001: “Bunny Mark”... is this your new name?
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124102009_From_Role124: “Bunny Mark” still needs some finishing touches.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201057_From_Role124001: ...Eating this, it feels like I've seen the Milky Way.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202038_From_Role124001: ...I hope that means we lived up to everyone's expectations.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202035_From_Role124001: So much time has passed in the blink of an eye. Even this place has transformed from an abandoned construction site to the beautiful greenway we see now.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202022_From_Role124001: We would come up with strange gadgets without any clear purpose and talk about the new food stalls that opened up near the school.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202114_From_Role124001: If collapse syndrome gets me one day... this little Sea Bunny is proof of my existence.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201011_From_Role124001: Actually... Maybe I should say that it's even more home than home?
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124203085_PlayerOption_ToRole124: No can do. I still have work at the Astral Sanctuary.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124203037_From_Role124: Sorry. I was exhausted from work...
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204024_PlayerOption_ToRole124001: Why don't we go for a walk?
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202107_From_Role124001: In fact, with better equipment, I'll be able to help even more people!
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204057_PlayerOption_ToRole124001: Why don't we go in and take a look?
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204064_From_Role124001: Something's off... Navigator, are you hiding something from me?
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201027_From_Role124001: Believe me when I say that I've sampled food from hundreds, if not thousands, of food stalls.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124203069_From_Role124: Not for one person, but for many people. For generations, even. These many memories intertwined into “culture”, which they dedicated their lives to preserving.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124102010_From_Role124: Don't worry. It's just a few technical details!
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201025_From_Role124001: To tell you the truth, I've been invited here as a guest judge.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202032_From_Role124001: I wonder how Erica and the gang are doing...
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202007_From_Role124001: That said... sigh... I guess we won't be able to play survival games here anymore.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201083_From_Role124001: But... Hey! Wouldn't it be better with a little bit of protein?

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124203071_From_Role124: Sometimes, in order to move forward, we need to leave something behind... But at the same time, we also need to remember the past.

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201115_From_Role124001: But I have faith that you'll make the right choice. We're good partners, after all!

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202112_From_Role124001: Protecting precious memories is your job, isn't it?
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124101007_From_Role124: Keeping silent? Hmm... You're a careful one.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124101040_PlayerOption_ToRole124: Let's start by having a chat.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204067_From_Role124001: First, you invite me to my school's open day...

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204112_From_Role124001: Guh... I don't know what to say...

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202047_From_Role124001: It's nothing complicated. All we need to do is play hide and seek!
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201005_From_Role124001: Things haven't been so lively in a while!
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201132_From_Role124001: Sigh... Making decisions can be hard at times, but you were so decisive! I wish I could be so cool... You've gotta teach me!
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201049_From_Role124001: Mhmm! It's good to be confident, but don't underestimate the creativity of your young and hungry competitors!

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124204023_From_Role124001: Sigh... Navigator, what are we gonna do? We can't celebrate without the guest of honor...

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201114_From_Role124001: Mhmm... To be honest, I'm having a hard time with this final decision.

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124202111_From_Role124001: Mhm... I've made up my mind.
AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124201119_From_Role124001: Mmm. Good choice, Navigator! Skewers and soda are the ultimate form of street food!

AVGEvent_KokonaShiki.Row124203053_From_Role124: Hehe... Looking at all this stuff makes me feel like a kid again.

AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201041_From_OtherRole: April 15 (crossed out), April 16... Area 89 (crossed out), Area 88... bombs successfully played at the demolition site.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201043_From_OtherRole: April 16, Area 88 demolition, poor fortune: I was lost all morning. Turns out the objective wasn't in the video store? I bought one of Kanami's new records to try and turn things around.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201044_From_OtherRole: May 3, Windy Town assault, poor fortune: Why do frag grenades look so similar to healing mines? At least I have Kanami's record to keep me company. Hoping for my luck to change soon.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201046_From_OtherRole: June 16, Port Euler demolition, good fortune: The demolition mission and fan meetup happened to be right next to each other! Finally, some good luck... I didn't even get lost once!
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201045_From_OtherRole: June 1, rescue mission, unclear fortune: I got lost again, so I went to Kanami's concert. Believe in that light, chase that light, and keep believing that things will turn around one day!
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201047_From_OtherRole: ...This is the good luck my idol brings to me! (The last few words seem to be sparkling with gold dust.)
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101072_From_Role128: “Nosy and doesn't play by the rules,” “full of hidden strength,” and “one who has the power to deal with collapse syndrome all on their own.”
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101012_From_Role128: ...Though, I admit, most of it is purely rumor.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101009_From_Role128: ...So the storied Navigator has heard of me. I should be honored.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202016_From_Role128: ...Did you come here just for this?
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128204086_From_Role128001: ...I once made a pact with someone.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203069_From_OtherRole: ...Longing for the sun yet unable to gaze at it. Is that why she's dressed this way?
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202051_From_Role128: ...The Astral Sanctuary? Isn't that the place that treats patients with collapse syndrome?
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101065_From_Role128: ...This hobby or that, does it matter?
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202079_From_Role128: ...The wound was treated very well. You have my thanks. I didn't expect you to be so good at first aid.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128102006_From_OtherRole: ...Thank you, Navigator. I'll make sure to follow your instructions.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201033_PlayerOption_ToRole128: This work is too much for one person.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202015_From_Role128: It's just a flesh wound. No big deal.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128204026_From_Role128001: The greatest characteristics of the dagger are its sharp edge and its ability to be hidden.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101006_From_Role128: No need to worry, I'm not armed. We're here to parley.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128102042_PlayerOption_ToRole128: You're not the only disciple here.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203072_From_OtherRole: Is she ok? You said she was an ER patient, so it must be serious, right? Go on, then. Take her to the hospital!
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202028_From_Role128: Still, they did end up getting in a few...
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128204023_From_Role128001: As a beginner, you have to be prepared for monotonous training.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202024_From_Role128: Indeed. They planned to use me to get rid of the guards, then turn on me while I was weak to take the crystals all for themselves.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128102044_From_Role128: That won't do. I was the one who invited you, so allow me to serve the tea...
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202084_From_Role128: For the sake of The Scissors, I have to do my best. A sharp blade that remains sheathed is of no use to anyone.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203080_From_Role128001: Don't apologize. Thanks to you, I've finally gotten rid of the investigators.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202018_From_Role128: I took a small risk in performing my duties, that's all.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201061_From_Role128: I was careless and neglected this part of our work. Sure enough, if the leader doesn't set an example, their subordinates won't know what to do.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128102057_From_Role128: Perhaps it's just a coincidence, but... those orchids I planted have finally bloomed.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202020_From_Role128: So, I followed our source to the transport site to verify the truth of the report.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128102046_PlayerOption_ToRole128: We've become mentors and friends to one another, and that's precisely why...
AVGEvent_Lawine.128102000_PrologueTitle: A Mentor as Well as a Friend
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128204122_From_Role128001: I confess: I had other intentions when I asked to meet you. I have sparred with a lot of people in an attempt to calm my mind but to little avail.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202088_From_Role128: Thank you very much for your help today. If it wasn't for you, this mission might have been delayed.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202089_From_Role128: Today's meeting was rushed, and I could not host you properly. The next time we see each other, let's enjoy a cup of hot tea.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128102028_From_Role128: I asked you here today so that we could finish our ceremony from last time.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202023_PlayerOption_ToRole128: They were also after the crystals?
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202026_From_Role128: They best remember the feeling of my pulse blade on their skin.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201035_From_Role128: One must inspire others by taking the initiative.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101074_PlayerOption_ToRole128: These rumors are just exaggerations, Lawine. Don't be led astray by gossip...
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101076_From_Role128: But, we wouldn't have asked you to be our “guest” if we didn't recognize your strength, Navigator.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203086_From_Role128001: But in the end, she's exactly like them. A bunch of hypocrites.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202025_From_Role128: But I wasn't going to let them win that easily!
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203018_From_Role128001: Now, P.U.S is bringing down the hammer. They've got investigators combing this place for signs of our activity.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128204119_From_Role128001: But I won't be helpless facing her again. That's for sure.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128102037_From_Role128: But, Navigator, please allow me this toast!
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101023_From_Role128: We won't treat a “guest” with inhospitality.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128204077_From_Role128001: As a beginner, you were able to parry my attacks with ease... What kind of tactics did you utilize?
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128204017_From_Role128001: I would like to teach it to you as a token of my appreciation.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203048_From_OtherRole: See the person in the photo? That's Lawine, the Executor of The Scissors.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201007_From_Role128: I suppose you got the request to meet. I wanted to talk a bit about how you've been doing, just like last time.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202055_From_Role128: Thank you for your kindness, but I can do it myself. I have more experience treating wounds.

AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202011_From_Role128: This thing? They're the spider plant seeds I ordered a few days ago.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128102031_From_Role128: It's a tradition of my family dōjō. When passing on one's legacy to a disciple, it is customary for the disciple to hold a ceremony as a show of respect and gratitude. We can do this through tea.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202034_PlayerOption_ToRole128: Let me take a look at the wound, just to be safe.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201053_From_Role128: No need for that. I'll be revising these reports myself.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201055_From_Role128: We made quite a few mistakes in our last battle. The team ended up in a sticky situation and suffered injuries as a result.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201066_From_Role128: Swift as the wind and agile as thunder... this is the speed we need to defeat P.U.S.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201054_From_Role128: A report is not meant to be a diary. Clearly, they've gotten lost in the weeds.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202033_From_Role128: It's not much. The blood will clot soon enough.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128101005_From_Role128: Pleasure to meet you, Navigator. I'm Lawine.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203025_From_OtherRole: Lawine... You're not getting away this time!
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128202019_From_Role128: I got a report that the PUS was making a secret shipment of purified crystals.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128201060_From_Role128: This is not difficult work. As you can see, some people are just lazy.
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203010_From_Role128001: It's you... but why are you dressed up like that?
AVGEvent_Lawine.Row128203097_From_Role128001: You were going to pick up some goods, right? I'm happy to come with you if you don't mind.
