Select "Mixed" to trigger actions with either a press or holding.
ST_Setting.MaxFPS_2: Determines the max in-game frame rate.
ST_Setting.RedDotColor_2: You will receive a red dot notification when you obtain an item of the selected quality or above. This setting will take effect the next time you log into the game after it is configured.
ST_Setting.VerticalSensitivity_2: Adjust how vertical movement compares to horizontal movement.
ST_Setting.SettingSideAndFly_2:
On ground: Enter a side-step stance.

In air: Enter a gliding state.
ST_Setting.AutoFireMaxDistance4_2: Determines the secondary weapon auto-ADS distance. When this distance is exceeded, auto-ADS is triggered.
ST_Setting.MBVerticalSensitivity_2: Adjust how vertical sensitivity compares to horizontal sensitivity.
ST_Setting.AutoFireMaxDistance2_2: Determines the marksman rifle auto-ADS distance. When this distance is exceeded, auto-ADS is triggered.
ST_Setting.AutoFireMaxDistance3_2: Determines the bolt-action rifle auto-ADS distance. When this distance is exceeded, auto-ADS is triggered.
ST_Setting.VoiceInputMode_2: Determines the squad/room voice chat mode.
ST_Setting.AutoFireMaxDistance1_2: Determines the light weapon auto-ADS distance. When this distance is exceeded, auto-ADS is triggered.
ST_Setting.Opt_Oyro_Value3_T: Determines gyroscope vertical sensitivity relative to horizontal.
ST_Setting.GamePad_TriggerBlindSpot_2: Divides left and right trigger travel into five zones: .2, .4, .6, .8, and 1.0. Configure this setting to modify trigger travel.
ST_Setting.ResponseCurveValue_2: Affects the aiming curve when aiming with the right joystick.
ST_Setting.OutsideBlindAngle_2: Configures the size of the outer deadzone when aiming with the right joystick.
ST_Setting.56: Changes to language settings will take effect after restarting the game. Are you sure you want to exit the game?
ST_Setting.Opt_Opro_Value2_T: Determines the gyroscope global sensitivity multiplier.
ST_Setting.Opt_Oyro_Value2_T: Determines the gyroscope global sensitivity multiplier.
ST_Setting.MaterialQuality_2: Higher material quality requires more VRAM.
ST_Setting.ModelDetailQuality_2: Determines the level of model detail.
ST_Setting.RenderMode_2: Forward rendering is more performance-efficient, while deferred rendering offers better visual quality.
ST_Setting.SSRQuality_2: Determines the quality of reflections. Higher quality improves detail and smoothness.
ST_Setting.EffectQuality_2: Determines the detail level of particle effects.
ST_Setting.FrameRateLevel_2: Determines the max frames rendered per second. Higher frame rates provide better quality at the cost of performance.
ST_Setting.TextureStreamingSpeedQuality_2: Determines the async load speed of texture streaming.
ST_Setting.TextureQuality_2: Higher texture quality requires more VRAM.
ST_Setting.AutoJumpDelayTime_2: Determines the auto-jump delay when wall-sticking.
ST_Setting.MBAutoJumpDelayTime_2: Determines the auto-jump delay when wall-sticking.
ST_Setting.Opt_Opro_Value3_T: Adjusts how much the gyroscope moves vertically relative to the horizontal sensitivity.
ST_Setting.AutoInWallDelayTime_2: Determines the wall-stick delay when forward wall-sticking.
ST_Setting.FlyAndAutoInWallDelay_2: Determines the wall-stick delay when glide wall-sticking.
ST_Setting.MBFlyAndAutoInWallDelay_2: Determines the wall-stick delay when glide wall-sticking.
ST_Setting.UIVolume_2: Determines the volume of sound effects when interacting with the UI.
ST_Setting.InnerCrossHairOpacity_2: Determines the opacity of the inner crosshair.
ST_Setting.InnerCrossHairOffset_2: Determines the offset of the inner crosshair.
ST_Setting.InnerCrossHairThickness_2: Determines the thickness of the inner crosshair.
ST_Setting.InnerCrossHairLength_2: Determines the length of the inner crosshair.
ST_Setting.CrossHairCenterOpacity_2: Determines the opacity of the center crosshair.
ST_Setting.CrossHairCenterThickness_2: Determines the thickness of the center crosshair.
ST_Setting.OuterFrameOpacity_2: Determines the opacity of the crosshair outline.
ST_Setting.OuterFrameThickness_2: Determines the thickness of the crosshair outline.
ST_Setting.OuterCrossHairOpacity_2: Determines the opacity of the outer crosshair.
ST_Setting.OuterCrossHairOffset_2: Determines the offset of the outer crosshair.
ST_Setting.OuterCrossHairThickness_2: Determines the thickness of the outer crosshair.
ST_Setting.OuterCrossHairLength_2: Determines the length of the outer crosshair.
ST_Setting.InGameVolume_2: Adjusts background music volume in multiplayer and tutorial levels.
ST_Setting.LobbyVolume_2: Adjusts lobby background music volume; also affects story background music volume.
ST_Setting.GameVolume_2: Determines the volume of gunshots, footsteps, skills, and other in-game sound effects.
ST_Setting.Wall2D_2: Move freely on walls after wall-stick.
ST_Setting.Jump_2: Determines whether you jump or air jump.
ST_Setting.SensitivityMode_2: When "Acceleration" is selected, view rotation speed increases with swipe speed.
ST_Setting.ButtonStyle_OpenAimMode_2: Select how ADS is triggered by the designated key.
ST_Setting.ButtonStyle_ShoulderMode_2: Select how shoulder fire is triggered by the designated key.
ST_Setting.InterruptReloadMode_2: Select the method to interrupt a reload. Mixed Interrupt: Use the reload or fire button to interrupt reload (does not cause the character to fire).
ST_Setting.Gyro_2: Determines the conditions for gyroscope usage. When the gyroscope is on, rotate the device to rotate the camera angle.
ST_Setting.SystemAnnouncementVoice_2: Select the voice for system annoucements.
ST_Setting.StringOptMode_2:
Determines the stringification controls.
Independent Mode: Do not simplify stringification controls.
Gesture Mode: Merge wall-stick and stringification controls into a single button.
Default: Use the most streamlined button controls.
ST_Setting.Switch_FireRotationAbility_2: Drag the screen to rotate the camera when tapping the right fire button.
ST_Setting.RightFireMode_2: ADS when tapping the right fire button.
ST_Setting.Switch_AimModeRotate_2: Drag the screen to rotate the camera when tapping the ADS button.
ST_Setting.Switch_SlideRotationAbility_2: Drag the screen to rotate the camera when tapping the stringify button.
ST_Setting.Switch_ShoulderModeRotate_2: Drag the screen to rotate the camera when tapping the shoulder-fire button.
ST_Setting.Switch_JumpRotationAbility_2: Drag the screen to rotate the camera when tapping the jump button.
ST_Setting.EnemyStrokeColor_2: Changes the outline color of enemies.
ST_Setting.LeftFireMode_2: Selects the condition for display of the left fire button (fixed to tap to fire).
ST_Setting.VoiceEffect_Mobile_2:
Choose how in-game sounds like footsteps, gunfire, and ability effects are presented, with each option offering different 3D spatial effects.
 
HRTF: 3D surround sound via headphones with sound distinguished between the front and rear. Make sure to disable other 3D sound programs when using HRTF. 
 
7.1 Surround Sound: If supported, expands the sound field to distinguish sounds from all directions for more precise sound localization. 
 
Dolby Atmos: If your device or environment supports it, experience immersive Dolby Atmos sound that envelopes from above and around you, placing you at the forefront of the game. Enjoy an intense and thrilling atmosphere as if you're transported into the game itself.
ST_Setting.VoiceEffect_2:
Choose how in-game sounds like footsteps, gunfire, and ability effects are presented, with each option offering different 3D spatial effects.
 
HRTF: 3D surround sound via headphones with sound distinguished between the front and rear. Make sure to disable other 3D sound programs when using HRTF. 
 
7.1 Surround Sound: If supported, expands the sound field to distinguish sounds from all directions for more precise sound localization. 
 
Dolby Atmos: If your device or environment supports it, experience immersive Dolby Atmos sound that envelopes from above and around you, placing you at the forefront of the game. Enjoy an intense and thrilling atmosphere as if you're transported into the game itself.
ST_Setting.SpatialAudioTypeMB_2:
Use spatial audio effects for in-game sounds.

If you encounter audio lag, try lowering the spatial audio setting. If you can't hear gunshots or footsteps, there may be a hardware compatibility issue. Try disabling spatial audio or switching to HRTF.
ST_Setting.SpatialAudioType_2:
Use spatial audio effects for in-game sounds.

If you encounter audio lag, you may be able to resolve the issue by lowering the spatial audio.
If you cannot hear gunshots, footsteps, and/or enemy ultimate voice lines, there may be compatibility issues. Try disabling spatial audio or changing the audio output to stereo or HRTF.
ST_Setting.SmartAutoInWall_2:
Determine how the character will stringify and wall-stick when near a valid wall.
Forward wall-stick: When the character is near a valid wall and continues to move forward, they will automatically wall-stick after a short delay.
Left wall-stick: When the character is near a valid wall, a wall-stick indicator will appear above the joystick. Drag the joystick to this indicator to auto wall-stick (when possible).
Manual wall-stick: You must tap a separate button to wall-stick.
ST_Setting.FlashBangColor_2: Choose the screen effect color for flashbangs.
ST_Setting.Switch_ClickedSmiteMode_2:
Toggle how to use melee weapon heavy attacks.
Fixed Button: Press the fire button for light attacks and the secondary fire button for heavy attacks.
Toggle: Press the secondary fire button to toggle between light and heavy attacks when using the fire button.
ST_Setting.WindowsAudioAPI_2:
Select the underlying API for the audio system (effective after restarting the game).
Auto-select: Tries XAudio2, WASAPI, and DirectSound in sequence, using the first supported API.

If you encounter audio issues that persist after adjusting spatial audio and output settings, there may be system or hardware compatibility problems. Switching the audio API configuration may resolve the issue.
ST_Setting.ButtonStyle_SprintMode_2:
Hold: When auto sprint is disabled, hold the sprint button to sprint and release to walk. When auto sprint is enabled, hold the sprint button to walk and release to sprint.

Toggle: Your character initially moves according to the auto sprint setting. Press sprint key to switch between walk and sprint. The toggle remains even after the character stops moving.
ST_Setting.ButtonStyle_MBSideMode_2:
Hold: Hold to sidestep.
Toggle: Press to toggle sidestep.
ST_Setting.ButtonStyle_MBFlyMode_2:
Hold: Hold to maintain glide.
Toggle: Press to toggle glide.
ST_Setting.Switch_TeamChat_2: The team voice channel includes all 5 members of your team.
ST_Setting.GamePad_Switch_GyroScope_2:
Activates gyroscope for supported devices only
(experimental)

ST_Setting.ExtraShoulderViewStartTime_1: Shoulder Fire FoV Horizontal Trigger Time
ST_Setting.ExtraShoulderViewVerticalSpeed_1: Shoulder Fire FoV Vertical Excess Rate
ST_Setting.ExtraShoulderViewHorizontalSpeed_1: Shoulder Fire FoV Horizontal Excess Rate

ST_UIActivities.Text_Info_1_Text:
*All rewards may undergo quality updates. Please refer to the final release version.
*Make sure to use the same account when the game officially launches.
ST_UIActivities.TxtDuration_Text:
1. During the event, complete quests to earn Battle Pass experience rewards.
2. During the event, the Experience Store unlocks once your Battle Pass experience is full.
3. During the event, after your Battle Pass experience is full, your extra experience can be used to change items in the Experience Store.
4. When the event ends, your remaining experience will be converted to Dream Tokens and sent to you via mail.
ST_UIActivities.RichTextBlock_210_Text:
<Chat-Self>Strinova Closed Beta Test: Superstring Rewards, </><Rank-Red>select a reward for time-warping, and it will be yours when the game officially launches!</>

Join Meredith and complete the seven-day quest to receive your reward on the <Rank-Red>eighth day</>!
ST_UIActivities.TxtShopDesc_Text: <Outline_Yellow16>During the event,</> your extra Battle Pass experience can be exchanged for the following items
ST_UIActivities.2024Anniversary_Text_6: You can exchange play points for souvenirs.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_138_Text: Unlock the Starter Pack with your first Top-Up of any amount or type.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_6_Text_1: The invitation code for early entry can only be obtained by Navigators who have mastered stringification.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_2_Text: During the event, log in each day to claim a reward. Collect all rewards by logging in for 7 days. After collecting all rewards, the event ends on the next login. Rewards are automatically claimed, so be sure to check them.
ST_UIActivities.FirstChargeRules_Content_1: Receive a Starter Pack after completing your first top-up of any amount.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_RoleFree_Text: Free to use for all roles
ST_UIActivities.2024Anniversary_Text_7: Collect play points to unlock stories.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_7_Text: Welcome to Strinova, we wish you a wonderful gaming experience.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_7_Text_1: Every Navigator may assist up to three friends in entering Strinova.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_313_Text: Open daily for 7 days to obtain all rewards
ST_UIActivities.Text_Info_Text: Log in daily to unlock one reward each day, for up to 7 rewards in total. On the eighth day, you can choose one item to time-warp and receive it when the game officially launches.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_48_Text: Tap to claim your daily Bablo Crystal rewards
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_5_Text: Strinova is still under construction and there may be instability and reverse-stringification areas.
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_123_Text: Complete a Top-Up of any amount to unlock the following rewards:
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_233_Text: The item has been sent to your future account
ST_UIActivities.Txt_ActivityDesc_Text: Complete the quest to generate an activation code to invite a friend to stringify and enter the world of Strinova!
ST_UIActivities.TextBlock_6_Text: Every beat of the notes guides us closer to each other.

ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.YouCanAlsoGetSegmentNotesToday: You may collect more notes today
ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.Txt_PhaseFlipRuleDes_Text: Scratch two chocolate banana boat patterns to enter the next area
ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.TextBlock_6_Text: When you scratch two stickers of the same themed pattern, you earn the reward(s) of the scratch card and unlock the next one, resetting the scratch card progress.
ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.TextBlock_Text: Congratulations! You have obtained all the rewards. Your remaining Dessert Coupons can be exchanged for
ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.TextBlock_89_Text: Collect Dessert Coupons to scratch for patterns and earn exclusive rewards
ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.TextBlock_164_Text: The exciting dreamland and the delicious dessert kingdom, two locations that only exist in dreams have merged into one! Countless visitors are eager to take part in the grand opening of the Strinova Par Dessert Carnival. Having found an admission ticket by accident, the Navigator starts a sweet journey of dreams.
ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.TextBlock_4_Text: During the event, complete event quests in the Fun Fair Booklet to obtain Dessert Coupons.
ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.TextBlock_5_Text: Collect Dessert Coupons to scratch for specific stickers at the Sticker Exchange, in order to redeem event souvenirs.
ST_UIActivitiesAmusementPark.TextBlock_8_Text: After unlocking all milestone rewards, remaining scratch cards can still be used to draw prizes at the Dessert Coupon Exchange.

ST_UIActivitiesCheongsam.TalkPage_Text2: Press anywhere to advance the conversation.

ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_90_Text: 1. Participate in matches (except custom matches) during the event to obtain the event item drop at the end of each round: Spring Wishcoin;
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_Text: 2. There are 5 types of <Red-Bold16>Spring Wishcoins</>. Up to 10 <Red-Bold16>Spring Wishcoins</> may be obtained by players daily;
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_1_Text: 3. Collect many different varieties of Spring Wishcoins to fuse into Spring Blessing Pack in the Spring Blessing Pack interface (up to 15 times);
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_2_Text: 4. <Red-Bold16>Spring Wishcoins</> can be <Red-Bold16>gifted to or received from friends meeting certain criteria up to 5 times per day;</>
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_3_Text: 5. Collect enough Spring Blessing Packs to achieve event milestones and milestone rewards;
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_4_Text: 6. Friends data may be subject to a 2-minute delay;
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_5_Text: 7. The [Visit Loved Ones] page displays gifting data within the last 120 pages.
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.RichTextBlock_6_Text: 8. Event data refreshes daily at 6:00 AM
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.TextBlock_4_Text: a. In Escort mode the payload will periodically release wishcoins as you progress, one of which can be picked up on approach
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.TextBlock_5_Text: b. Wishcoins will be randomly dropped at the conclusion of other event modes;
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.TXT_Surplus_Text: You can gift <Red_Feedback>4</> more times today
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.TextBlock_168_Text: No friend gift data to show
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.TXT_Time_Text: Event start time: February 2, 2024 to February 22, 2024
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.TXT_LevelTips_Text: Reach game Lv. N to unlock the current event (M/N)
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.TextBlock_Text: The coming spring has inspired festivalgoers to arrange an elaborate parade float, enhancing the celebrations to new heights...
ST_UIActivitiesCNYCollectBlessings.TextBlock_Text1: The coming spring has inspired festivalgoers to arrange an elaborate parade float, elevating the celebration to new heights. The crowds are hoping for much more than a frivolous gift - an omen of good luck and chance to redirect some good fortune their way in the coming year.

ST_UIActivitiesCNYFireworkStory.TextBlock_3_Text:
1. Complete Festival Preparation quests to earn Harmony Coins

2. Collect Harmony Coins to purchase limited-edition New Year items from the Treasure Emporium

3. New Year items can be gifted to Superstring Agents in the Dormitory

4. Festival Preparation quests refresh every 7 days during the event

5. Collect New Year items to increase Preparation Progress and earn Milestone Rewards and Story Keys

6. Use Story Keys to unlock event stories in the Harmony Promise

Happy Spring Festival, Navigators!
ST_UIActivitiesCNYFireworkStory.TextBlock_67_Text: You automatically accumulate Harmony Keys. View the number of keys you have acquired in Harmony Promise.
ST_UIActivitiesCNYFireworkStory.TextBlock_Text: Spend Harmony Keys during the event to unlock exclusive story events from this screen/character dormitory screen

ST_UIActivitiesCNYLuckyLottery.TextBlock_3_Text: Sign in daily during the event to participate in a draw and unlock a reward each day.
ST_UIActivitiesCNYLuckyLottery.TextBlock_5_Text: Go to [Past Draw Results] to view previous event draw results;
ST_UIActivitiesCNYLuckyLottery.TextBlock_7_Text: ·Participate in 14 draws to obtain all rewards;
ST_UIActivitiesCNYLuckyLottery.TextBlock_4_Text: Rewards auto-claimed. Be sure to take a look!
ST_UIActivitiesCNYLuckyLottery.TextBlock_Text:
Good Luck Draw! Spring Fortune is here~
Hey there, remember to come here daily to draw your lucky gift!
Who's the gift provider? Hmm... that's a secret!
ST_UIActivitiesCNYLuckyLottery.Txt_OpenPage_Text: Click on the Fortune Box to draw lots

ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_4_Text: 1. During the event, complete adventure quests to receive event items - notes.
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_7_Text: 2. Consume the specified number of notes to unlock event levels in 【Rehearsal】.
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_8_Text: 3. During the event level, you also to follow the rhythm and input the correct notes at specified locations to perform the entire musical score of the level.
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_9_Text: 4. When you have played every note in the level, you will obtain the level rewards and unlock the corresponding background story.
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_10_Text: 5. After unlocking all levels, the remaining notes can be exchange for items at the 【Exchange Store】.
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_6_Text: Yet Bai Mo has greatly underestimated the opinions of these gentlemen, and their rift I fear is so great as to have destroyed any promise of this great performance. It is for this reason I especially wanted to pass this letter to you...
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_205_Text: The preparation is over. Time to enjoy the xxx music performance!
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.ParticipateInActivityProcessUnlocking: Unlocked by participating in the event
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_102_Text: Input the correct notes within the specified time to complete the level
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_Text: At the start of the new year, a special invitation from Urbino was handed to you.
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_5_Text: This message comes from Bai Mo, head of the Urbino Business Alliance. Having been inspired to celebrate the New Year with music, Bai Mo has called for talented musicians from far and wide to participate in the event.
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.Text_13_Text: Click anywhere to return to home screen
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.TextBlock_Text1: Johann Sebastian Bach is widely regarded as one of the greatest religious composers of all time who devoted his life to the meticulous craft of composition. Despite possessing few material valuables, Johann left behind a remarkable body of work that has guaranteed his enduring influence on future generations.
ST_UIActivitiesConcert.PleaseCompleteThePreviousChapterFirst: Please complete the previous chapter first

ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.Text_13_Text: 1. During the event, on New Year's Eve, crew members will send out exclusive greeting card. Please remember to claim it.
ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.Text_12_Text: 1. During the event, complete 【Adventure Quests】 to receive event items - safety apples.
ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.Text_11_Text: 2. Consume the specified number of apples to unlock event levels in [Coloring Book] and complete script drawing.
ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.Text_14_Text: 2. Greeting cards refresh daily at 6:00 AM
ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.Text_10_Text: 3. While coloring, you have to fill the colors of the drawing using a paintbrush. When the progress reaches 100%, the coloring level is completed.
ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.Text_7_Text: 4. Complete a drawing level to unlock its story and rewards in “Safety Day Adventure”.
ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.Text_5_Text: 5. After unlocking all levels, the remaining safety apples can be exchanged for items at the 【Exchange Store】.
ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.ContentText_Text: Christmas is so much more wonderful when you can celebrate it alongside those you care about, which is why I'm so lucky to be with you this festive season! Thanks for hosting and making us feel truly special. Merry Christmas!
ST_UIActivitiesFairyTale.TextBlock_2_Text: Log in tomorrow to claim the next greeting card

ST_UIActivitiesHallomas.ExplainContent1:
It's almost time for the annual Spookfest! To celebrate and boost sales, Urbino is hosting a three-day street parade. Participants are encouraged to dress up as their favorite characters, and the audience will vote to decide which lucky participant wins a mysterious gift.

Show off for a chance to win awesome rewards. Three lively days are coming to Commercial Street!

But before the celebration begins, something peculiar happens. Spectators report spotting a real ghost among the parade participants. Festival-goers grow uneasy, worried about whether the parade can still proceed as planned. As a staff member, it's your job to identify the "ghost" from a list of suspects...

ST_UIActivitiesHallomas.Rule3: Unlock all stories to access the Spooky Sweet Shop, where you can exchange Pumpkin Lollipops for Basestring rewards.

ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_1_Text: To promote her café, Audrey embraced the Navigator's suggestion by wearing a maid outfit as a promotional strategy.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_5_Text1: Following the Navigator's advice, Yvette decided to connect with a wide range of people. Her research revealed that people in service roles, such as maids, are quite effective.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_4_Text: The Navigator is organizing a maid-themed idol event for Kanami.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.YvetteWordMap_2: Some rude guests do cause trouble, but I don't think it's a big deal. It's all research at the end of the day, and Fay makes sure they behave.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.MaidSelectedItem_Audrey_bp_maidDesc: To promote a café under her management, Audrey heeds the Navigator's advice, putting on a maid outfit as a method of promotion.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.KanamiWordMap_2: This outfit? It's my way of saying thanks for always having my back! Keep cheering me on, and I'll keep dazzling you~!
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.AudreyWordMap_2: W-What? Handling guests is... of course, something I can manage just fine...
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.MaidSelectedItem_Yvette_bp_maidDesc: Heeding the Navigator's advice, Yvette has decided to get to know people of all kinds. Based on her research, she has concluded that service personnel such as maids seem to be more useful.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.AudreyWordMap_3: As my strategist, it's only fair that you receive the best service. After all, providing excellent assistance is a maid's responsibility, right?
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.KanamiWordMap_3: Hmm~ The response has been fantastic! How about I add a maid outfit to my next idol event? What do you think?
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.Text_40_Text: Complete superstring quests to unlock exclusive rewards.

ST_UIActivitiesMaid.MaidSelectedItem_Kanami_bp_maidDesc: The Navigator is organizing a maid-themed Kanami Idol event.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.AudreyWordMap_1: Go ahead, take a good look! B-But make sure to try our new coffee... please?
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.YvetteWordMap_3: I want to learn more about people... especially you, Navigator.
ST_UIActivitiesMaid.YvetteWordMap_1: I'm... doing what you suggested, Navigator. I believe studying the service industry, such as by being a maid, might be more fitting for my research.

ST_UIActivitiesMarineOrganism.ExplainContent3:
1. Participate in the [Adventure Plan] to collect [Coral Branches].
       2. Collect [Coral Branches] to unlock [Treasure Hunter's Diary] stories and receive rewards the first time you read them.
       3. Perform a [Deep Sea Hunt] and spend [Coral branches] to get random items and drift bottle stories.
       4. Once you obtain all [Deep Sea Hunt] rewards, a new unlimited reward table will become available.
       5. Head to the [Bottled Tales] page to view your collected drift bottle stories.
ST_UIActivitiesMarineOrganism.ExplainContent1:
Surf the waves, build sandcastles, soak up the sun—create unforgettable memories.

Explore shipwrecks, uncover ruins, embark on daring quests—hunt for mysterious treasures.

The summer islands, far from the city's hustle and bustle, have become the hottest vacation spot and a treasure hunter's dream! Adventurers and tourists alike take on the roles of ancient sea creatures, face various trials, and piece together treasure maps to uncover legendary loot.

In this paradise of white sands and turquoise waves, what awaits you and the girls? Thrilling surprises or unexpected scares?

ST_UIActivitiesMeredith.TextBlock_1_Text:
[Event Overview]
 The expedition team arrives at the edge of the True Wilderness, and their communication devices begin to flash.
 Intel shows a signal deep within the Wilderness, accompanied by a surge of crystal energy.
 It all feels like a carefully laid trap. But it’s too late to turn back now—there's something out there, whether energy or a lost soul.

[Event Time]
 TBD

[Event Rules]
 1. Complete quests during the event to earn Energy Points and recharge the pyramid.
 2. When the pyramid reaches a certain Energy level, you have a chance to receive rewards and clues.
 3. At 100% Energy, obtain a Superstring Selection Gift Box.
 4. After summoning and unlocking a Superstring, exchange remaining Energy Points for items.
 5. Daily quests refresh at 7:00 AM (UTC+0).
ST_UIActivitiesMeredith.HeadText_1_Text: Complete quests to collect Energy. Once you reach 100% Energy, you can get a Superstring Selection Gift Box.

ST_UIActivitiesNowYouSeeMe.TextBlock_157_Text:
The Philharmonia Hall is about to host a one-of-a-kind concert featuring the renowned singer, Kanami! Naturally, the Navigator received a VIP ticket, signed personally by the idol herself. According to reliable sources, Kanami will also debut her magic show at this concert!

   Meanwhile, Bai Mo invites the Navigator to the Twilight Auction, sponsored by the Bai Group, at Kidd Hall. Rumor has it that the auction features unique treasures and collections valuable even to the Navigator!

   With both irresistible events happening simultaneously, whose invitation will the Navigator choose? Since they're both at Laurel Hall, one could attend half of each...

ST_UIActivitiesSalon.TxtContent_Text:
Despite her intimidating aura, speaking with Flavia was surprisingly easy. However, I couldn't help but notice that she had been subtly controlling the subject of the conversation.
It was as if she was trying to tell me something.
“On a side note, there was this charming and mysterious woman who showed up at the bar after hours. I even managed to get her name.”
“I wonder... did that all happen, or was I just dreaming?”
Flavia smiled softly: “I don't want to get into the business of plugging one lie with another, so I'll tell the truth.”
“Please, don't hold back.”
Flavia lowered her eyes and shot a serious look at the poker table: “It wasn't me. The cards were already on the table when I arrived.
I'm simply trying to solve the mystery... care to join me?”
I couldn't say no.
ST_UIActivitiesSalon.TxtDesc_Text:
My eyes wandered around the bar before being quickly drawn to a woman sitting on a single sofa, playing poker.
Everything about her screamed “mysterious”, from the smile on her lips and her hidden gaze
to her figure flickering under the light. Could this be my client?

ST_UIApartmentInformation.TextBlock_Content_Text: I'm just an ordinary girl with nothing special. Growing up in a small town, my parents were always busy. I had no toys, nor friends to hang out with. I felt lonely all the time. But later on, I discovered anime and video games! Albeit still alone, I was no longer lonely. Anime and video games showed a whole new world full of wonders! It was only natural for me to venture into Strinova by myself. Never could I imagine that I was entering a two-dimensional world. I made a vow to protect, so I volunteered to become a P.U.S investigator!

ST_UIAuth.RichTextBlock_37_Text:
To protect the physical and mental health of minors, and in accordance with the “Notice on Further Strengthening the Management and Preventing Minors from Indulging in Online Games” issued by the National Press and Publication Administration, here are some of the rules:

1. Users who have not completed identity verification are not allowed to play the game.

2. Minors are only allowed to play the game <Division_Type>during the hours from 8 p.m. to 9 p.m. on Fridays, Saturdays, Sundays, and public holidays</>.

3. Players under <Division_Type>8 years of age</> are not allowed to top up. Players aged <Division_Type>8 and above but under 16 years of age</> are limited to a maximum single top-up amount of <Division_Type>50</> and a monthly cumulative top-up amount of <Division_Type>200</>. Players aged <Division_Type>16 and above</> but <Division_Type>under 18 years of age</> are limited to a maximum single top-up amount of <Division_Type>100</> and a monthly cumulative top-up amount of <Division_Type>400</>.

ST_UIAuth.Text_3_Text: According to the “Notice on Preventing Minors from Indulging in Online Games” issued by the National Press and Publication Administration, all online game users are required to register their game accounts using valid identification. Minors will be subject to restrictions imposed by anti-addiction features.

ST_UIBattlePassBackground.RichTextBlock_Content_Text: <White14>It seems Michele·Lee stumbled on an old classified file on 【Unexplained Incidents】 that the Sistine had been trying their best to keep hidden.</></br></br><White14>The higher the level of authority required, the more overwhelming the urge to read something without permission.</></br><White14>The files revealed a shocking story on the fatal retirement of the previous PUS Captain, the many ambushes of The Scissors terrorists, and the civilians whose reputations may have been tarnished thereunder...</></br><White14>A succession of names thought to provide at least part of an answer turn out only to be part of a much bigger unofficial smokescreen associated with a mysterious photo.</></br><White14>The truth is far stranger than any of those supposedly in the know have realized, a fact noted with some amusement by the multidimensional entity responsible.</>

ST_UICareerCareerRank.Txt_RankTips_Text: 1. The top 1000 players of Quark rank and above are shown in the server-wide rankings; the top 100 players are shown in Team Deathmatch and Escort rankings. All rankings refresh hourly.
ST_UICareerCareerRank.TextBlock_121_Text: 2. Go to System Settings > Basic to configure your location privacy.
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_2_ContentText1:
<Black22>1. The basic star rules remain the same: winning team gains 1 star, losing team loses 1 star. Strinovium Points are an additional star-gaining rule.</>

<Black22>2. After a match, regardless of the outcome, you gain Strinovium Points. Strinovium Points = Mode Score + Win Streak Bonus + Match Ranking Bonus + Skill Bonus (if your team's overall skill is above the average for that rank).</>

<Black22>3. Star Protection: When your Strinovium Points reach a certain threshold, Star Protection activates. If you lose a Ranked Match, it will deduct the corresponding amount of Strinovium Points instead of losing a star. The points consumed for Star Protection increase with Rank.</>

<Black22>4. Bonus Star: When your Strinovium Points hit the cap, winning another Ranked Match will consume some of your current Strinovium Points and add 1 star. The points consumed for this are equal to the Star Protection points for your current Rank.</>

<Black22>5. Match Ranking Bonus: 1st place (5 points), 2nd place (4 points), 3rd place (4 points), 4th place (3 points), 5th place (3 points).</>

<Black22>6. Win Streak Bonus: 1 win (3 points), 2 wins (8 points), 3 wins (13 points), 4 wins (18 points), 5 wins and above (23 points).</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.RichTextBlock_37_Text: <Black22>The ranked mode is the most challenging mode of Strinova. Every season, players who dare to take the challenge will receive epic rewards. You have to reach Lv. 5 and own at least 5 heroes to play the ranked mode. Keep leveling up and unlocking heroes, and you can start your legendary journey.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_1_ContentText: <Black22>In ranked mode, you earn a star for each victory and lose a star for each defeat by default. After your star count is full, earning another star increases your division or rank. When you have no stars left, losing another star demotes you to the next division or rank.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_5_ContentText: <Black22>During each season, once you reach a certain rank, you can obtain the corresponding rewards. For details on rewards and their corresponding rank, please visit the Season Rewards page.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_ContentText1:
<Black22>Players are assigned to one of several ranked divisions, broadly indicative of a player's skill level.</>
<Black22>Division lowest to highest are: Substance, Molecule, Atom, Quark, Origin Stringification, Superstring, Strinova.</> <Black22>The Substance to the Superstring divisions are further subdivided into grades, each accompanied by a number of stars. See here for further details in the Rank Map.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_3_ContentText:
<Black22>When a player reaches Strinova, their maximum star limit will be increased to 9,999. The system performs a check every hour, and if a player has not played any ranked matches during the previous 7 days, they will lose 1 star.</>
<Black22>The server updates the rankings of all players every hour. The top players in the rank of Strinova will be listed on the leaderboard. This information will be sent to all the players on the server.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_4_ContentText:
<Black22>Season Duration: Each season lasts for approximately three months.</>

<Black22>Your rank and division reset after the end of each season. After the previous season ends, everyone has a chance to start over. Your starting position in the new season will be determined by your highest rank from the previous season.</>
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_1_ContentText1:
<Rank-Title>1.</> When your Strinovium Points reach a certain score, a portion of them will be deducted first to offset losing a star after a Ranked match loss.
<Rank-Title>2.</> When your Strinovium Points are at the maximum limit, winning a Ranked match will consume some points to grant an extra star.
<Rank-Title>3.</> Each rank has different Strinovium Points limits, and the amount deducted for losses or consumed for wins varies.


<Rank-Title>Bonus Scores:</>
<Rank-Title>1. No AFK:</> 3 points.
<Rank-Title>2. Match Score Rankings:</> Earn Strinovium Points based on your score ranking within your team. <Rank-Red>1st place:</> 24 points, <Rank-Red>2nd place:</> 18 points, <Rank-Red>3rd place:</> 13 points, <Rank-Red>4th place:</> 9 points, <Rank-Red>5th place:</> 6 points.
<Rank-Title>3. Win Streaks:</> <Rank-Red>1 win:</> 3 points, <Rank-Red>2 wins:</> 8 points, <Rank-Red>3 wins:</> 13 points, <Rank-Red>4 wins:</> 18 points, <Rank-Red>5+ wins:</> 23 points.
<Rank-Title>4. Skill Compensation:</> 10 points. Awarded when your rank is significantly lower than the enemy team's average, regardless of the outcome.
<Rank-Title>5. Effort Compensation:</> 50 points. Given to outstanding players in case of defeat or a draw.
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_2_ContentText:
<Rank-Title>1.</> Upon reaching Superstring rank, Ranked matches switch to a points system. Points increase or decrease based on performance and outcome after each match.
<Rank-Title>2.</> On promotion from Quark to Superstring rank, Strinovium Points convert to Superstring Points at a <Rank-Red>20:1</> ratio.
<Rank-Title>3.</> If Superstring Points fall to 0, your first loss triggers rank protection. Another loss will demote you to Quark I.
<Rank-Title>4.</> If you don't play a Ranked match for <Rank-Red>7 consecutive days</>, you'll lose 30 Superstring Points, down to a minimum of 0.
<Rank-Title>5.</> Once you reach 200 Superstring Points, ranking in the top 500 promotes you to Singularity rank. Falling out of the top 500 demotes you back to Superstring rank.
<Rank-Title>6.</> Superstring and Singularity ranked players can only queue solo or as a duo.
ST_UICareerCareerRank.WBP_RankDropBox_Widget_ContentText:
<Rank-Title>Participation Rules:</> Reach <Rank-Red>Lv. 10</> to unlock ranked matches.
<Rank-Title>Season Duration:</> Each season lasts around 2 months. At the end of the season, rewards are based on the highest rank achieved. A new season begins with placement matches to determine your initial rank.
<Rank-Title>Rank Structure:</> There are 9 major ranks, each with various divisions and Strinovium Points thresholds.
<Rank-Title>Promotion and Demotion:</> Earn a promotion after filling all stars in a division and winning one more match, gaining an extra star. Exceptional Navigators may skip a sub-rank.
Demotion occurs after losing all stars in a division and one additional loss.
<Rank-Title>Rank Protection:</> Players in the Substance or Molecule rank will not lose any stars after losses. Players in the Proton rank will not be demoted after losing all stars in a division.

ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP8_Card1_Content: A girl who dreams of breaking the shackles of fate, she is currently under special observation as a user of a new String Body.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP7_Card1_Content: A talented master perfumer. With her help, the Scissors seem to have gained a new lease of life.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP8_Card2_Content: To ensure that the Snowveil District Music Festival goes smoothly, The Scissors are carrying out an urgent transport mission...
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP8_Card3_Content: The Urbino Business Alliance is hosting a celebration, inviting everyone to dress as their favorite character for a night parade. But strange things keep happening... Could something unusual have slipped into the festivities?
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP7_Card3_Content: With a mysterious letter, you became the new employer of the "Shark". How does one become stronger? What is true strength? These questions are awaiting your answer.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.Text_RankDesc_Text: Your excellent performance has made you stand out among many mighty warriors. Your future breakthrough will surely revolutionize the entire competitive scene.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP7_Card2_Content: Looking back, the New Dimensions Initiative guided humans to Strinova and built a new home in the vast expanse...
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_Text: Rewards will be sent out via mail
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP101_Card2_Content: A masked high school girl, with flames dancing at her fingertips, silently safeguards the streets of Preton.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP7_Card4_Content: Scarlet Awakening Warrant is now available. Advanced Warrant rewards include: Fragrans - Desert Explorer and Eika - Fire Dancer. Advanced Warrant Plus also grants an exclusive case reward: V-06 Fragrance Interwoven.
ST_UICareerNewSeason.NewSeason_BP8_Card4_Content: Corrosive Genesis Warrant is now available. Advanced Warrant rewards include: Yugiri - Feather Dancer and Flavia - Special Agent. Advanced Warrant Plus also grants an exclusive case reward: W-02 Spiral Soul.

ST_UICareerNewSeasonSeasonAward.TheAwardIsSentByEmail: Rewards will be sent out via mail

ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_40_Text:
A lone shark seeking comfort, this new duelist prefers to be left alone.
 Reticent and hiding behind a mask, they are a skilled warrior, having studied the habits of sharks.
Make way for the shark!
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_32_Text: Lawine frequently hits archery dojo. You can practice archery, watch flowers, and have tea here.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_28_Text: As a result of Operation Crimson Blade, more explosion attacks have taken place in various locations. What hidden crisis lies among them...
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_36_Text: Kokona, the inspector from PUS will meet with the Navigator in the dormitory. Kokona is a reliable veteran, but what is she like in real life? As the two get to know one another, the Navigator will uncover Kokona's hidden, softer side.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.Text_40_Text1: A free and lonely young shark, she is a duelist employed by Urbino. As long as the battle is interesting enough, she cares not for moral standards, eliminating all the targets.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_8_Text:
"Echoes" sound in the air, and streams of string vibration spread throughout the sky.
Under the cover of battle between P.U.S and The Scissors,
something quiet is happening.
What could it be? The curtain lifts.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_Text: In order to prevent PUS from stealing top secrets, The Scissors is determined to destroy crucial lab data...
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_5_Text:
Yvette meets you for the first time in the dorm!
Though little is known about this P.U.S researcher, her mysterious aura is intriguing. But with genuine interaction, even the thickest ice can melt.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_8_Text2:
Want to know the secrets behind the stage?
Then why not meet Kanami in person?
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_2_Text:
In the face of defeat, how can The Scissors reclaim the city's transit system
from Painting Utopia Security?
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_190_Text1:
An energetic high school student.
Adorned in a mask, she protects the streets of Preton
with the power of fire.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_8_Text1:
At The Scissors' invitation, the Astral Sanctuary
finds themselves a new city - Preton.
The calamity from 18 years past, the fate of P.U.S and The Scissors...
Everything will be decided here.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_2_Text2:
A new season has begun!
Earn your glory in the heat of battle!
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_5_Text1: Recently, Yvette has become hooked on Gomoku, and it just so happens you’re familiar with it too. Think you can beat her? Head to Yvette's dorm for a face-off!
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_190_Text:
A sunny young man dressed in fashionable attire,
this hacker travels the world with Urbino as his stage.
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.SeasonPlotWhisperingDarkClouds: Season story: Whispers in the Dark
ST_UICareerNewSeasonUpdateContent.TextBlock_2_Text1:
This is a young and hip neighborhood.
Bai Mo enjoys skating here by the parkour route.
If you need to find him, this is the place!

Summer_333_Lv_1.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId107: There's no need for such hostility. Art is boundless. I need you two to remain civil during the event!
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId107: See, Yvette's got a feeling for atmosphere.
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Yeah! It's “Summer Hits,” an annual music festival hosted by Urbino.
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId108: Why is she changing clothes for this occasion?
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Navigator, let's go enjoy the event together!
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row8_PlayerOption1: Feels like the Navigator's job is getting harder and harder...
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId107: I, Maddelena, am honored to be given responsibility for the event's layout and equipment together with the Navigator.
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId108: Think nothing of it. Protecting the city is P.U.S' job. I'll keep an eye on The Scissors.
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId107: As for maintaining order and controlling the audience... I leave it to you!
Summer_333_Lv_1.Row2_PlayerOption1: What kind of group is this?

Summer_333_Lv_2.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId108: You three, stop slacking around! Finish your work if you want to chat!
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Hey! You can't leave me alone with all this work.
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Oi, it's not like I'm the only one playing. Isn't everyone having fun?
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Sorry, sorry... I was busy collecting materials.
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId108: She doesn't reply to the group chat or my private messages. Where's she gone?
Summer_333_Lv_2.Row10_PlayerOption2: Stabbing me in the back now? You traitor!

Summer_333_Lv_3.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId108: No matter if it's Ming or that other guy.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId107: You're just in time. I just got a bunch of skewers and takoyaki.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Let's change the subject. The ice cream's going to melt.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Thank you all for the hard work. I'll treat you guys today.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId107: I know. This must be the feeling of loneliness that follows a big celebration.
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId108: I'm fine, just a little moved... The music of The Scissors is quite beautiful.
Summer_333_Lv_3.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId108: Looks like things are coming to an end...
Summer_333_Lv_3.Row5_PlayerOption1: It's probably not the main point, right?

Summer_333_Lv_4.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId107: But why has Nobunaga traveled so far?
Summer_333_Lv_4.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Navigator, Yvette, did you guys take a photo just now?
Summer_333_Lv_4.Row2_PlayerOption1: We would like to preserve this moment for eternity.
Summer_333_Lv_4.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId108: I'm just a steward. Maintaining order and monitoring The Scissors is my real job.
Summer_333_Lv_4.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId107: There we go! I'll hold onto this photo forever... it's my souvenir.

Summer_333_Lv_5.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId107: The one thing left to find is... the sea...
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Eh? What's wrong, Yvette? Have you been hiding with the Navigator all this time?
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId107: All good, then. I didn't expect that your abilities could be used like this...
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Just a small gift for everyone.
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Navigator, are you there? Have you seen Yvette? I can't find her at the beach or any of the food stalls.
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId108: Can you help me look, Navigator?
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId108: I'll ask around. You can head to the venue, Maddelena.
Summer_333_Lv_5.RowStart_TextContent_FromRoleId107: By the way, where's Yvette? I've been trying to find her for a while.
Summer_333_Lv_5.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId107: Sigh... I can't find it anywhere. I'm getting worried.

The special edition "Spring Blessing" of "Polaris," inspired by the motif "Ascendance," embodies the courage and determination Celestia has gradually built up through past hardships.

“For the patients, I won't back down anymore. This is what my predecessors taught me.”

【“This is no ordinary wishing star. It always flies toward my desired target.”】

"That was such a blast! I need to touch up my makeup... Heh.”
Weapon.10106106_Tips:
Specialized Polaris model. This firearm was a gift obtained from the Space Expericenter in Polaris. Designed in the shape of a space station, it tells the tale of mankind's longing for the endless expanse. It's not exaggeration to say this firearm is industrial art made manifest.

【"For an endless sky, I offer my endless yearning."】
Weapon.10106201_Tips: A customized version of the "Polaris." The red rose across the barrel symbolizes the fearsome sword of a knight in an ancient tale of heroism.

A customized version of the "Polaris." The red rose across the barrel symbolizes the fearsome sword of a knight in an ancient tale of heroism.

“As people are like roses, so are swords.
With fire as their soul and steel as their bones.
Amidst the intensifying gunfire, roses blossom.
The crimson maiden on the battlefield has long accepted her fate to wither.
In her brief moments of rest, gently caressing the flowers,
to whom will she leave the garden of roses in her heart?”
Weapon.10106105_Tips:
The "Polaris" custom model cleverly incorporates medical themes, seemingly implying anti-war ideals...

They save lives not in the hope of praise, nor do they raise their guns to fight.
In front of them lies war, and behind them, peace.
Weapon.10106104_Tips:
Artistic Polaris model. References to fairy tales from old Earth reveal a surprising innocence in this weapon's designer.

【Wrapped in fragile dreams, a child's innocence beams. Kindness and purity, in our essence, gleams.】
Weapon.10403108_Tips:
A customized version of the "Champion" featuring enhanced sensitivity to light. Whether for photography or firing bullets, it performs in perfection.

“This moment is worth capturing, don't you think?”
Weapon.10403201_Tips:
A personalized "Champion" model with a pristine barrel, basking in the Grove family's glory and victories. Fervent flames flow through it, symbolizing Lord Grove's indomitable spirit.

To protect her family, the young girl took this gun onto the battlefield. Now, with the newly upgraded weapon in hand, there's composure and determination in her once-furrowed brow. The answers to those questions? As before, seek them through bullets.
Weapon.10403106_Tips:
A customized artistic version of the "Champion," adorned with strings of the Guqin, concealing the pinnacle of technology under the classic design.

"In drifting clouds, her garments I find; in blossoms, her visage so fair.
She shines by the balustrade, caressed by the dew-laden air.
Should Jade Mountain's peak hold her not in view.
Then beneath the moon, on gemstone terrace, she'll appear anew."
Weapon.10403104_Tips:
The custom "Champion" design by Audrey incorporates four unique musical elements. Each string of notes plays the same melody with distinct tones.

"It's a piano, a saxophone, an old vinyl spinning in solitude, capturing the faded memories of the past. I don't know what eras this gun has witnessed, but the moment it fires, the past becomes crystal clear."
Weapon.10403105_Tips:
The artistic custom version of "Champion" is inspired by old Earth's local folklore, vividly showcasing a deeply cultural aesthetic.

“In ignorance of bountiful years true,
Chasing the fox god, a myth in view,
Finding none but illusions and emptiness.”
Weapon.10111005_Tips: The "Rebel" series features a striking color contrast and a pattern design resembling a swift, powerful lightning bolt, perfectly capturing the spirit of rebellion and defiance.

Surely, once winter passes, the arrival of spring is not far behind."

【This is what it feels like to break free from all constraints!】

"Isn't it normal for a bar owner to carry a gun? If danger ever strikes, I need to clear a path to safety for my guests."

"Why are there price tags on these wild spring onions?? Reiichi!!"

"No prey seen by this eagle will ever escape."
Weapon.10102201_Tips:
A customized model of the Rebelflame, with a thunderbolt-shaped barrel through which electricity surges like a dragon. Its gunshot is as loud as its owner's reputation. Rumor has it that a single shot from this weapon shakes the land like thunder, echoing through the world.

The Scissors' long-standing tradition of welcoming newcomers with stories has evolved into a martial arts showcase, drawing listeners from all over. As the vice-captain and speaker for the assault team, he eagerly shares tales of the captain's exploits.
During one session, while recounting the Wasteland Thunder story for the 50th time, a young listener unexpectedly interrupts, requesting to hear the adventures of the Thunderous Dragon outsmarting criminals.
Just as he prepares to answer, a figure in a battle suit makes a dramatic entrance.
“P-Prepare for combat? Now? What's the mission, Captain?”
“Simply put, it's a battle of wits against criminals!”
After grabbing a bag of chips, the figure waves to the young listener.
“Seeing is believing! Today, you'll witness it firsthand!”

A manga dialogue box suddenly popped out from the gun, right in the middle of an intense firefight.
And just like that, what was an intense affair quickly gained an air of levity.】

But now,
the gilded masks remain elegant; the ancient power as strong as ever,
a shimmering brilliance from a distant past.】

"Who would have thought that a little spark could light up the entire universe?"

The design of "Wildfire" draws inspiration from the latest high school fashion trends. Flames shooting from the barrel symbolize youthful energy.

"Woo! Fire it up!"

The modified "Sawtooth" has been by Fuchsia's side since childhood. Its cold barrel holds warmth in her heart.

"The path to mastery is not one I walk alone."
Weapon.10108201_Tips:
A customized edition of the Sawtooth, inspired by the skeleton of a shark from old Earth. Equipped with high-performance light elements, recreating the might and solitude of the deep-sea beast.

Strinova's marine ecosystem is broken. Among the ocean's migratory creatures, only the sharks survived. Yet, they have lost their sharpness and strength, and even their sense of smell is fading. Bionic technology was needed to restore their former glory.
When Fuchsia received the modified Sawtooth, she couldn't help but admire the exquisite attention to detail.
“No big deal. It's only a scaled replica of a shark skeleton salvaged from the deep sea.”
The gunsmith remarks with a nonchalant raise of his eyebrow.
“The deep sea? Are there still sharks out there?
“Sadly, there remains just one... My colleague from Bionic Tech mentioned it's been extremely agitated lately."
Sharks are typically solitary and composed, so why this sudden agitation? Fuchsia is eager to uncover the reason behind the shark's unusual behavior.
Weapon.10108109_Tips:
Custom Sawtooth model. Lightweight yet powerful, it works like a vacuum to efficiently clear away any unwanted 'trash and debris'.

[Cleaning like a maid, but with bullets.]

【"The setting sun... It's glorious."】

yvette_131_Lv_1.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId131: The next time you're here, Navigator, I'll be notified immediately.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Whenever I purchased heavy equipment, the delivery person would always end up complaining. But Fay says they've never had that happen.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row9_TextContent_FromPlayer: It might be because it made a sound like Yvette's voice...
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Ah? Is that so...? The human world is such a complicated one...
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I thought... rather than spending so much time to mentally prepare myself, I could get Fay to meet strangers on my behalf.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Anyway, I'll have an authentication system installed by the entrance.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row11_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I gave Fay a little “trial”. The results were actually pretty good.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Did you mistake Fay for me? Or did you think I'd turned into Fay...
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId131: It seems that Fay has better social skills than Yvette.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId131: And for some reason, things started to go more smoothly.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Fay told me you seemed surprised.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Fay says, it seems that you misunderstood something just now...
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row16_PlayerOption2: Sociability might not be the most important thing here.
yvette_131_Lv_1.Row20_PlayerOption1: I look forward to the next visit!

yvette_131_Lv_3.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Things like, “When can data visualization devices be mass-produced? Could you develop an enhanced version?”
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId131: No, I'm not blaming you, Navigator...
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId131: In my opinion, emotions are private, personal feelings.
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I lack the courage, nor am I prepared to show my emotions to people.
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row15_PlayerOption1: What would Yvette like to know?
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row20_TextContent_FromRoleId131: But isn't it irresponsible of me to have developed such a device...
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row27_TextContent_FromPlayer: As a price for going a bit too far last time.
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row22_TextContent_FromPlayer: Maybe we should start by limiting the usage?
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row25_TextContent_FromRoleId131: If someone asks again, I think I'll be able to deal with it... probably.
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Perhaps I haven't figured it out yet. That's why I lost my cool.
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row4_TextContent_FromRoleId131: So... All of PUS asked me about it today...
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row23_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Mmm. That's how it should be.
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row7_TextContent_FromPlayer: Sorry, it was just too fun...
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId131: After what you've done, Navigator... you're not snickering behind the screen, are you?
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId131: That's why you let everyone try it...
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId131: This design has not been officially made public, but it's all out now...
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row21_PlayerOption1: Got it. Until we come up with a better solution...
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row11_TextContent_FromPlayer: I didn't consider Yvette's feelings. It won't happen again.
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Should something like “emotions” really be displayed with such ruthlessness, as if one were performing surgery?
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I should be the one who's sorry.
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row24_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Fortunately, other than the device given to the Navigator, I am also working on another one...
yvette_131_Lv_3.Row10_PlayerOption1: Is that so? Sorry, I don't know anything about it.

yvette_131_Lv_5.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Just thinking about the fact that Fay ran away makes it hard to breathe...
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row14_PlayerOption1: Don't be afraid of things that haven't happened, Yvette.
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row10_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Yvette's also trying to convince herself over and over again...
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row4_PlayerOption2: Is Yvette afraid that Fay will leave?
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Are you awake? I can't sleep...
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId131: You're right! Not only had I failed to properly reward Fay, but I kept staring at her as if she were a suspect...
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Mm-hmm, that's what Fay said as well...
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I'm scared... So, I placed Fay right next to my pillow.
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row21_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I'm going to buy Fay a cup of milk tea!
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId131: No way... I don't make Fay feel pressured...
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row4_PlayerOption1: I thought Fay didn't run away from home?
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row11_PlayerOption1: Fay is not going to sleep well tonight.
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row8_PlayerOption1: Fay only wants you to be happy.
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row16_TextContent_FromPlayer: Fay left to surprise you later on. That's all you have to know.
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row17_TextContent_FromPlayer: Fay got your favorite milk tea. In return, come out and play with your good friend!
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row22_TextContent_FromRoleId131: As for rewards... How about I buy Fay some new clothes? Or should I make some myself? But I only know how to make dresses...
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row23_PlayerOption1: Let's put that aside for now.
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row15_TextContent_FromPlayer: It'll only make you even more troubled.
yvette_131_Lv_5.Row5_TextContent_FromRoleId131: In that case... I'm not sure, either. It seems that the fears from earlier were justified...

yvette_131_Lv_7.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId131: No, no... calling it a gift seems rather pretentious...
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId131: The apartment complex I used to live in no longer accepts new tenants. You can't obtain a new access card. Here is a spare one.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row16_PlayerOption1: Does Yvette see “returning home” as an escape?
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I should get Sir Bear something as a reward...
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row29_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Your words... I'll consider them carefully.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row23_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Mmm. When I returned today, I did feel a lot more relaxed.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row21_TextContent_FromPlayer: Once home, I'll be able to set out again with a full battery.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row19_PlayerOption1: You should be happy going home.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Sir Bear is fantastic! My dream has been well protected!
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row28_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Sir Bear is quite the philosopher.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row24_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I thought it was because I slept well...
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row26_TextContent_FromPlayer: I really like the place where Yvette was raised. I hope that you will, too.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Maybe you can come find me here.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Every time I return home, I feel annoyed that I've retreated into my shell again...
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row12_TextContent_FromPlayer: I feel burdened by responsibility all of a sudden.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row13_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Even though I don't want to think about it... If one day, Yvette really disappears...
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row4_PlayerOption1: Let's give Sir Bear our thanks!
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row25_PlayerOption1: You slept well because you were home, no?
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I will probably need your help.
yvette_131_Lv_7.Row20_TextContent_FromPlayer: You wish to go home when you're sad because you feel safe there.

yvette_131_Lv_9.Row10_PlayerOption1: ...You've suddenly become scary behind the screen!
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row5_PlayerOption2: It's not like you can't go into stealth at all...
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row3_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Have you any idea as to why I can't go into stealth in front of you and only you, Navigator?
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row2_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Why... Why did it turn out like this...
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row8_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Just stand far away and you'll be able to see. Yvette's there, totally invisible to the others.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row12_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Huh... I want to figure out what's going on.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row6_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Hmm... I can hide part of my body, but my presence can still be detected.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row19_TextContent_FromRoleId131: In the Navigator's heart, is Yvette a transparent being with no secrets?
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row14_TextContent_FromRoleId131: Certainly, Navigator. However, it may cause significant issues should it fail on others on the battlefield.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row17_TextContent_FromRoleId131: I'm wondering if it's because you know me so well, Navigator, that you're able to see through my stealth.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row20_PlayerOption1: It's an existence that I'll never ignore.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row18_TextContent_FromRoleId131: After all, I would like to tell you everything and share all I have...
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row7_TextContent_FromRoleId131: You don't even need to get close.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row15_TextContent_FromRoleId131: That's never happened before. I've tried it many times, so don't worry.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row21_TextContent_FromPlayer: If there's really a situation where I can't be stealthed when fighting an enemy, I'll just have to take things head on.
yvette_131_Lv_9.Row9_TextContent_FromRoleId131: If this goes on... we can only...
